Commentary: Off the mark is Rohit Sharma! Right on the first ball too. Back of a length, around off, nipping away slightly, Rohit taps this through covers and collects a single.
On a length, around off, coming back in, KL taps this to point and looks for one. He is rightfully sent back by Rohit.
In the channel outside the off pole, KL shoulders arms on this occasion.
Length outside off this time, Rahul watches the ball go past him to the keeper.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! This is a great start by England and they have struck in the very first over. This is just what they would have wanted after the Lord's Test. This is well set-up by Jimmy, as in the previous ball, he bowled a ball in the channel outside off, which nipped back in significantly and hence, Rahul went to play at this, keeping in mind the inswing. Usually, when there is a delivery in such a channel, KL has been wary and has left it, but this time, he goes chasing after this and pays the price, as this delivery nipped away late and caught the edge. James Anderson runs in and serves a fuller ball, in the fourth stump channel, gets it to move away as well. KL Rahul looks for the big, booming drive through the off side, but only manages an outside edge, which is easily gulped down by Jos Buttler behind the sticks. The crowd is loving it and India's opening stand does not last the first over!
Howout: c Jos Buttler b James Anderson

Commentary: Good length ball, around off, Pujara prods ahead and blocks the ball out. A top start by Jimmy!
Fuller ball, outside off, Sharma watches it go past him to Buttler. No ball called as Ollie Robinson has overstepped.
Another one in the channel outside off, Sharma leaves it untouched.
Good length, closer to off, Rohit does not play at this.
Outside off, left alone.
Angles into the pads, Rohit looks to flick but gets a leading edge, which safely goes to the point region.
Another leave as this was bowled outside the off pole.
On a length outside off, Rohit lets it go through to the keeper.
Fuller, way outside off, Pujara is not bothered by it and leaves.
Short of a length, on the body, Pujara dabs this to the leg side.
Fuller, around off, Pujara looks to defend, but the ball nips inwards and takes the inside edge and hits him on the pad.
Outside off on a length, away movement again, Pujara defends inside the line and gets beaten.
Around off, defended back onto the deck.
Outside off, left alone.
Outside off, length ball, the ball nips back in sharply, as Rohit shoulders arms, and the ball whistles past the off pole.
Fuller, in the channel outside off, Rohit looks to play at that but gets beaten.
Leg bye. This is bowled on the pads, Sharma looks to nudge this to the leg side but misses and the ball takes the pad and goes to the leg side. The batters take a leg bye.
Around off, CP pushes this through covers for a run.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Back of a length, coming back in, RS looks to fend it out but misses and gets hit on the pad high. An appeal but turned down.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! What a start this is for Anderson and England. They have struck again and India's wall, Pujara, has been breached. Anderson probes with his line and length and makes Pujara play at this, which proves to be his undoing. Again, he dishes a couple of inswingers and poses a question on Pujara's mind, then, he serves an outswinger in the zone of uncertainty and gets the better of Pujara. On a length this time, around the off pole, the ball hits the deck and nips away beautifully. Cheteshwar Pujara pokes his blade at this, looking to defend, but the ball catches the outside edge, due to the away movement. Jos Buttler dives low to his right and pouches this. India have started off poorly and the crowd are loving it!
Howout: c Jos Buttler b James Anderson

Commentary: Fuller, outside off, nipping away, Virat shoulders arms.
Outside off, left alone.
In the zone outside the off pole, Kohli again makes a leave.
Way outside off, VK watches it sail past him to the keeper.
What an over by Jimmy! Another wicket for him. Fuller, outside off, Virat leaves it untouched.
Full ball, way outside off, angling away late. Rohit Sharma leaves it alone.
Good-length ball, around off. Rohit Sharma gets behind the line and blocks it towards backward point.
Length ball, coming back in late. Rohit Sharma defends it off the front foot to cover.

FOUR LEG BYES! Good-length ball, jagging back in, around the pads. Rohit Sharma misses the flick and it clips his pads towards the boundary ropes. Jos Buttler dives to his left but the ball beats him.
On a length, outside off. Rohit Sharma shoulders arms to this one.
Good-length ball, coming back in from off stump. Rohit Sharma gets forward to block this one.
Full ball, around off. Virat Kohli gets low and drives it through mid off to get off the mark as they take three runs. Moeen Ali gives it a chase and saves a run for his side.
Length ball, outside off. Rohit Sharma leaves it alone watchfully.
Full ball, way outside off. Rohit Sharma lets it go through to the keeper.
Length ball, angling in from outside off. Rohit Sharma shoulders arms to this one.
Another length ball, just outside off. Rohit Sharma prods forward but leaves it in the end.
Good-length ball, around off. Rohit Sharma gets behind the line and defends it towards the vacant cover region and takes an easy single.
Length ball, on off. Rohit Sharma drives it back to the bowler who gets a hand to it as the ball deflects towards mid off and they take one.
Length ball, jagging back in after pitching. Virat Kohli comes forward and defends it.
FOUR! Nicely done! Good-length ball, around middle. Virat Kohli tickles it towards fine leg for a boundary.
On a length, way outside off. Virat Kohli shoulders arms to this one.
Well bowled! Back of a length, just outside off. Virat Kohli looks to leave it alone but gets an under edge as the ball rolls away behind the sticks. No Ball called as Ollie Robinson has overstepped.
Full ball, outside off. Virat Kohli drives it towards the extra cover fielder.
Short of a length, outside off. Virat Kohli lets it go through to the keeper untouched.
BEATEN! Good-length ball, jagging back in from outside off. Rohit Sharma looks to poke at it but is beaten as the ball zips past his inside edge.
Back of a length, on middle. Rohit Sharma looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto his pads as there is some extra bounce on offer.
An inswinger, around off. Rohit Sharma comes forward to block this one.
Length ball, angling in from off. Rohit Sharma turns it towards mid-wicket off the front foot.
Good-length ball, outside off, moving away slightly. Rohit Sharma leaves it alone.
Length ball, around off. Rohit Sharma defends it to cover and collects an easy single to end the over.
Length ball, angling in late from middle and leg. Rohit Sharma turns it towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Good-length ball, jagging back in from middle. Rohit Sharma works it uppishly towards mid-wicket.
Length ball, around off. Rohit Sharma prods forward and blocks it to cover.
BEAUTY! Good-length ball, around the fourth stump channel. Rohit Sharma looks to defend but is beaten as ball holds its line and zips past his outside edge.
Back of a length, around off. Rohit Sharma taps it towards backward point.
Full ball, angling in late. Rohit Sharma defends it solidly off the front foot.
Well bowled! Back of a length, outside off. Virat Kohli is in two minds whether to leave or defend it but leaves it in the end as there is some extra bounce on offer for Jimmy.
Length ball, sprayed down leg. Virat Kohli misses the flick and the ball goes to the keeper.

TWO LEG BYES! Length ball, angling in from middle and leg. Virat Kohli misses the flick and gets it on the pad as the ball races away towards the boundary ropes. Sam Curran cuts it around and saves a couple.
Length ball, coming back in from off. Virat Kohli defends it off the front foot.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! This is a huge wicket for James Anderson and England, as they get to see the back of the Indian captain. In another episode of the Jimmy vs VK show, it is the English veteran who has come out on top again. Length ball, around the fifth stump channel. Virat Kohli plays a very loose-looking shot, as he looks to drive through covers but the ball nips away slightly, and he only manages an outside edge and Jos Buttler behind the sticks does the rest. Anderson is pumped up and India are three down inside the first hour of play and they are in some trouble now.
Howout: c Jos Buttler b James Anderson

Commentary: Length ball, angling in from middle. Ajinkya Rahane gets behind the line and blocks it watchfully.
Good-length ball, around off. Rohit Sharma taps it towards backward point.
BEATEN! Good-length ball, outside off. Rohit Sharma hangs his bat it and the ball whizzes past his outside edge.
FOUR! CLASSY! Overpitched ball, on off. Rohit Sharma comes forward and drives it straight back past the bowler for a boundary.
Short of a length, on off. Rohit Sharma blocks it solidly off the back foot.
Good-length ball, jagging back in just that little bit. Rohit Sharma defends it off the back foot.
Well bowled! Length ball, nipping in late from middle and leg. Rohit Sharma looks to defend but inside edges it towards fine leg as he is a bit late on it. They take a single.
On a length, on the fourth stump line, Rohit looks to block inside the line but gets beaten.
Short of a length, angling in, Rohit looks to work this to the leg side but gets hit on the thigh pad.
FOUR LEG BYES. Errs this time, does Jimmy. On a length, on the pads, Rohit Sharma looks to flick but misses and the ball takes the pad and runs away to the fine leg fence.
Fuller outside off, RS shoulders arms.
Gets behind the line of the ball and defends this one out.
Around off, angling inwards, on off, Rohit taps this to point. Comes ahead, but then yells a loud 'NOOOOOOO!' to his partner.
Slants a length delivery across the right-hander, Ajinkya looks to defend, but the ball angles away from his blade to the keeper.
An action replay of the previous delivery. Rahane gets beaten by the angle again.
Width offered outside off, Rahane dabs this to the point fielder.
Fuller in length, around middle, pushed to the fielder at short covers.
Closer to the off pole, on a length. Still not close enough for Ajinkya to play at this as he makes a leave.
Angles a length delivery across Rahane. He looks to leave it late, but the ball takes the under edge and bounces next to the turf.
Pitches it up and around off, Sharma pushes this to the leg side.
Outside off, no shot offered.

Serves a back-of-a-length ball this time, lands around off, sharply nips back in as Sharma is late in getting his bat down in time. The ball hits the thigh pad and lobs towards the slip cordon, where the fielder takes it. An appeal but nothing from the umpire. Root does not go for the review. A good choice as UltraEdge shows no spike.
Outside off, RS shows no interest to play at this.
A carbon copy of the previous delivery.
Around off, blocked.
On a length, around leg, the ball hits the deck and shoots up this time and Rahane gets pinged high on the pad. An appeal but turned down.
On off, pushed to the off side.
Around off this time, Rahane taps this to point.
Full, on off, AR works it to short covers.
Shortish this time, on the body, Ajinkya Rahane hops and nudges this to the on side for a run.
On middle, bounces slightly more than what Rohit anticipated, as he awkwardly fends it back onto the deck.
Floats it up around off, Rahane blocks it well.
Rahane gently prods forward and smothers this ball out.
A touch short, around off, AR pushes this to covers.
Rahane goes back into his crease and pushes this shortish ball to the off side.
Rahane goes back and pushes this back to Moeen.
Just a single from Moeen's first over! Flatter, on off, turning in, Rahane pushes this past mid off for an easy run.
Slanting across, on a length, around off, Rahane gets beaten as he looks to defend.
Outside off, AR dabs this behind point. He waits to see if there is a single there, as Rohit Sharma is down the track, looking for the run, but Rahane sends him back quickly.
Around off, kept out nicely.
Slightly behind the good length, around off, nips back in, AR looks to defend, but gets an inside edge back onto his pad. The ball lobs up, but lands safely next to Jinks.

FOUR! Rahane played that nice and late and gets a boundary. Will give him some confidence. On a length, outside off, Ajinkya Rahane goes back and waits for the ball to arrive, before then dabbing it past the backward point fielder. Haseeb Hameed gives it a chase but ends up on the losing side.
Drags his length back and serves a short ball, down the leg side. Ajinkya Rahane looks to hook it away but misses. Jos takes it and appeals but the umpire does not move.
Outside off, just pushed away to the point region.
Slower through the air, on middle, Sharma gets low and just paddles this to short fine leg for one.
On middle, clipped to the leg side for a single.
Flatter, on off, Rohit pushes this through covers and changes the strike.
Goes back and pushes it back to Ali, does Rahane.
Full on off, punched back to Ali again.
Good-length ball, darted on the pads. Rohit Sharma misses the flick and gets hit high on his pads. The ball rolls away towards the short leg fielder.
Length ball, angling in from middle and leg. Rohit Sharma turns it towards mid-wicket.
Full ball, on the pads. Rohit Sharma flicks it off his pads towards sqaure leg for a single.
Good-length ball, moving away late, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane leaves it alone.
Length ball, nipping away, from outside off. Ajinkya Rahane comes forward but shoulders arms to this one.
Well bowled! Good-length ball, around the fourth stump channel. Ajinkya Rahane looks to defend but is beaten as the ball zips past his outside edge. How often have we seen that today!
Starts with a back of a length, on middle and leg. Rohit Sharma misses the flick and gets hit on his thigh pad.
Good-length ball, jagging back in from middle. Rohit Sharma misses his flick again and gets hit on the pads.
Length ball, around off. Rohit Sharma drives it straight back to the bowler.
Good-length ball, angling away late after landing. Rohit Sharma gets behind the line to block it.
Length ball, around off. Rohit Sharma defends it solidly off the front foot.
Short of a length, on off. Rohit Sharma hops in the crease and blocks it out.
Back of a length, around off. Ajinkya Rahane defends it off the back foot to the cover region.
FOUR! Nicely done! Short of a length, down leg. Ajinkya Rahane rocks back and whips it towards fine leg for a boundary.
Length ball, on off. Ajinkya Rahane prods forward to block this one out.
Good-length ball, outside off, angling away after pitching. Ajinkya Rahane shoulders arms to this one.
Back of a length, just outside off. Ajinkya Rahane defends it towards backward point. No Ball called as Sam Curran has overstepped.
Length ball, on off. Ajinkya Rahane defends it off the front foot.
No ball again, as Sam Curran oversteps. Good-length ball, jagging back in from off. Ajinkya Rahane looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Short of a length, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane stays back and cuts it towards backward point for a quick run.

Good-length ball, around the fourth stump channel. Ajinkya Rahane looks to defend but gets an outside edge towards Joe Root at first slip. The ball does not carry as it was played with soft hands by Ajinkya.
Length ball, around off. Ajinkya Rahane defends it solidly.
Overpitched ball, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane squeezes it out to cover.
Short ball, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane punches it off the back foot to wide of the mid off fielder. Rohit Sharma wanted a single but he was sent back by his partner.
Short of a length, on off. Ajinkya Rahane gets behind the line and blocks it out.
Back of a length, around off. Ajinkya Rahane taps it towards backward point.
Starts with a full ball, outside off. Rohit Sharma reaches out and drives it through extra cover for a couple. Sam Curran gives it a chase and keeps it down to two.
Length ball, outside off. Rohit Sharma shoulders arms to this one.
Good-length ball, around middle. Rohit Sharma gets a bit squared up in his defense as the ball nips away slightly.
Good-length ball, outside off. Rohit Sharma works it towards the slip cordon with soft hands.
Length ball, jagging back in sharply. Rohit Sharma comes forward to defend but gets an inside edge onto his pads. England appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
Length ball, around off. Rohit Sharma comes forward to block this one out.
Good-length ball, on off. Ajinkya Rahane gets behind the line and defends it off the front foot.
Length ball, coming in with the angle, from off. Ajinkya Rahane blocks it well under his eyes.
Good-length ball, outside off, nipping away late. Ajinkya Rahane shoulders arms to it.
BEATEN! Length ball, around the fourth stump channel. Ajinkya Rahane prods forward to defend but is beaten as the ball whizzes past his outside edge.
Back of a length, on off. Ajinkya Rahane blocks it well off the front foot.
FOUR! Nicely done from Ajinkya Rahane. Length ball, strayed on the pads. Ajinkya clips it off his pads through the vacant fine leg region for a boundary.
Banged in short, around middle. Rohit Sharma looks to pull but gets a top edge towards fine leg for a run.
Good-length ball, jagging back in from middle. Ajinkya Rahane gets an inside edge onto his pads as he looks to defend it.
Length ball, strayed on the pads. Ajinkya Rahane works it off his pads towards fine leg for a couple. Ollie Pope comes around and stops a certain boundary.
Good-length ball, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane shoulders arms to this one.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Ollie Robinson has struck for England in the last over before Lunch and India are in deep trouble now. Good-length ball, around the fifth stump channel. Ajinkya Rahane hangs his bat at it and gets an outside edge towards Jos Buttler behind the sticks, who pouches it comfortably. Ollie Robinson gets rid of India's vice-captain, just when he was looking to steady the innings with his batting partner. England are bossing this game now and they will be a happier team going into Lunch on Day 1. With that, IT IS LUNCH ON DAY 1!
Howout: c Jos Buttler b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Length ball, strayed on the pads. Rishabh Pant flicks it off his pads towards square leg for a run to get off the mark.
Good-length ball, on off. Rishabh Pant steps out and taps it towards mid off for a quick run.
Length ball, moving away after landing, outside off. Rohit Sharma leaves it alone.
Full ball, way outside off. Rohit Sharma shoulders arms to this one.
Good-length ball, jagging back in late. Rohit Sharma prods forward to block this one out.
Short of a length, outside off. Rohit Sharma looks to poke but withdraws his bat at the last minute.
Length ball, way outside off. Rohit Sharma lets it go through to the keeper.
Length ball, outside off. Rishabh Pant looks to drive on the up but slices it in the end towards backward point where Rory Burns dives to his left to stop the ball.
On a length, outside off. Rishabh Pant taps it towards backward point.
Well bowled! Good-length ball, around the fifth stump channel. Rishabh Pant looks to defend but the ball zips past his outside edge.
Length ball, around off. Rishabh Pant prods forward and pushes it to mid on.
Back of a length, around middle. Rishabh Pant stays back to block it out.
A loud shout for LBW but the umpire turns it down! Good-length ball, around middle and leg. Rishabh Pant gets forward to defend but he misses and gets hit high on the pads.
Back of a length, around off. Rohit Sharma stays back and taps it behind square on the off side.
Lovely delivery! Good-length ball, around the fifth stump. Rohit Sharma looks to defend off the front foot but the ball goes past his outside edge to the keeper.

Length ball, on off. Rohit Sharma looks to defend but gets an inside edge back towards the keeper. Rishabh Pant looks for a single but is sent back by Rohit Sharma. Jos Buttler has a shy at the non-striker's end but he misses.
On a length, outside off. Rohit Sharma leaves it alone.
Length ball, angling in from off. Rohit Sharma defends it off the front foot.
A yorker, around off. Rohit Sharma digs it out.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Ollie Robinson gets rid of the dangerous Rishabh Pant and India are 5 down now. Another catch for Buttler and he has been a busy man in this Test so far. Pant has struggled to get into a good rhythm in this series so far and the same story continues. Back-of-a-length ball, angling away outside off. Rishabh Pant could have left it alone, but he decides to poke at this and gets an outside edge towards Jos Buttler, who takes his 5th catch of the innings. Ollie Robinson is delighted and England will look to get these remaining wickets quickly as India have a long tail.
Howout: c Jos Buttler b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Good-length ball, angling in from middle. Ravindra Jadeja stands tall and blocks it.
Length ball, angling away after landing, outside off. Jadeja leaves it alone.
Well bowled! Good-length ball, just outside off stump. Ravindra Jadeja sways away from the line of the ball.
Short of a length, around off. Ravindra Jadeja taps it to cover.
A Wicket Maiden! Length ball, around off. Ravindra Jadeja defends it solidly off the front foot.
Good-length ball, outside off. Rohit Sharma leaves it alone.
Length ball, coming in with the angle from off. Rohit Sharma blocks it to cover.
Good-length ball, strayed on the pads. Rohit Sharma gets an inside edge onto his pads as he looks to flick. The ball rolls away behind the sticks and they take one.
Banged in short, down leg. Ravindra Jadeja ducks under it.
Length ball, around off. Ravindra Jadeja defends it solidly.
Overpitched ball, just outside off. Ravindra Jadeja digs it out to mid off.
Short of a length, around middle. Rohit Sharma blocks it towards the on side.
Good-length ball, outside off. Rohit Sharma leaves it alone.
Back of a length, way outside off. Rohit Sharma shoulders arms to it.
Short ball, down leg. Rohit Sharma swivels and pulls it along the ground towards fine leg for a single.
Length ball, around off. Ravindra Jadeja gets forward and defends it back to the bowler.
Good-length ball, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja leaves it alone.
Short of a length, around off. Rohit Sharma blocks it out.
Length ball, way outside off. Rohit Sharma shoulders arms to this one.
Good-length ball, jagging back in from off. Rohit Sharma comes forward to defend this one out.
Length ball, outside off. Rohit Sharma taps it towards backward point off the front foot.

EDGED BUT SAFE! Good-length ball, outside off. Rohit Sharma pokes at it and gets an outside edge towards Jonny Bairstow at second slip, who dives low to his left. The ball did not carry to him as it was not played with hard hands.
Length ball, outside off. Rohit Sharma lets it go to the keeper.
Length ball, strayed on the pads. Jadeja misses the flick and gets rapped on the pads. England appeal but the umpire turns it down.
Well bowled! Good-length ball, just outside off. Ravindra Jadeja looks to defend but the ball whizzes past his outside edge.
Length ball, on off. Ravindra Jadeja defends it off the front foot.
Short of a length, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja lets it go through to the keeper.
Good-length ball, on middle and leg. Ravindra Jadeja prods forward to defend this one.
Good running between the wickets! Length ball, around off. Ravindra Jadeja defends it to cover and scampers through for a single.
Slants across a back-of-a-length delivery across the southpaw, Jadeja goes back and looks to defend, but gets beaten by the angle.
Fuller, on the pads, nudged to the short mid-wicket fielder. A loud 'NO!' by Jadeja.
On a length, close to the off pole, RJ pushes this towards point for a quick single.
Hurls a length ball on the pads, this is glanced neatly through square leg for a run.
Digs in a short ball around the body, RJ just sits under this one.
Good length, outside off, Jadeja takes a stride forward and pushes this to covers and rotates the strike.
Curran starts his new spell with a length ball on the pads, nudged to fine leg and one is taken.
NO BALL. On middle, tucked to square leg and Jadeja is handed the strike again, with a single. A no ball is called as Sam Curran stepped past the crease.
Full on off, RJ pushes it back to the bowler.
Lands it around off, but the ball hits the pitch and straightens. Jadeja looks to defend inside the line and the ball whistles past the edge to the keeper.
Outside off, left alone.
Short of a length, around off, the ball jags back in quicky and misses Jadeja's blade, but goes onto hit him near the unmentionables. No harm done, though.
Fuller outside off, Ravindra shoulders arms.
Around off, pushed to the cover region.

That looked close! On a length on off, Rohit taps this to the leg side and wants the run. Jadeja sends him back quickly as Craig Overton reaches the ball and whips it towards the wickets, as Sharma scampers back. Misses, though.
Pushed to the fielder at covers now.

OUT! CAUGHT! Oh, dear! The same story continues for Rohit Sharma. He looks to play the pull shot, but he gives an easy catch to the silly mid on fielder. He has played 105 balls, but he has put all of that down the drain as he gifts his wicket away. Craig Overton runs in and hurls a short delivery, around off, the ball does not come onto the bat nicely as Rohit Sharma looks set to play the pull shot. He miscues it and the ball takes the lower half of the blade and lobs towards Ollie Robinson at silly mid on, who will take this in his sleep. So, obviously, he does the same while he is awake. India slip further as they lose their sixth wicket!
Howout: c Ollie Robinson b Craig Overton

Commentary: OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Overton gets back-to-back wickets and England are on fire here. The hero of the Lord's Test, Shami, has to walk back for a golden duck. 67/7 - a depressing scoreline if you are supporting India. Back of a length this time, around off, Mohammed Shami hops and looks to defend, but only gets an outside edge. The ball goes to the right of third slip, where Rory Burns moves that side and pouches this. Craig Overton is on a hat-trick here!
Howout: c Rory Burns b Craig Overton

Commentary: Ishant Sharma survives the hat-trick ball! Around off on a length, a speedy ball, Sharma defends it to the off side.
Outside off, on a length, Jadeja leaves it alone.

OUT! LBW! Another one bites the dust and India are falling apart here. Wonderfully bowled by Curran and the only recognized batter has been sent packing. Sam Curran digs in a yorker this time, taking Jadeja by surprise. Jadeja gets his bat down late and misses as the ball takes the pad and goes to the keeper. A loud appeal and the umpire raises his finger. India have all three of their reviews left and so, Jadeja takes the review. No bat shows the UltraEdge. Ball Tracker shows THREE REDS. The on-field decision stays on and England just need 2 more wickets to bundle India!
Howout: lbw b Sam Curran

Commentary: OUT! LBW! BACK-TO-BACK! India are at 67/9 now! This time, Curran serves a length delivery around middle and leg, Bumrah looks to flick this to the leg side but misses. Curran appeals and runs away in celebration as the umpire raises his finger. Bumrah takes the review but it does not work out as UltraEdge shows no bat and Ball Tracker shows three reds. One more wicket away are the Brits. Sam Curran is on a hat-trick too!
Howout: lbw b Sam Curran

Commentary: NOT OUT! No hat-trick for Sam Curran! Full ball, angling in late from middle and leg. Mohammed Siraj misses the flick and gets an inside edge onto his pads. England appeal but the umpire turns it down. Joe Root opts for a review! The replays show that Siraj got a bat on it so the on-field decision stays.
Good-length ball, jagging back in from middle and leg. Mohammed Siraj swings hard but misses and gets hit on the body.
Length ball, in the slot, around off. Siraj hangs back and hits it back past the mid off fielder for a couple of runs.
Short of a length, on off. Ishant Sharma drives it uppishly towards the mid on fielder.
FOUR! Crucial runs for India. A full ball outside off. Ishant Sharma squeezes it past the slip cordon for a boundary. Dawid Malan gives it a chase but the ball wins.
Short of a length, just outside off. Ishant Sharma hangs back to defend but misses and gets hit high on his pads. England appeal but the umpire turns it down.
Full ball, outside off. Ishant Sharma digs it out towards gully.

Good-length ball, outside off. Ishant Sharma swings hard but only manages an outside edge towards Jonny Bairstow at second slip who jumps to take the catch but he drops it. They take a run as the ball goes past the slip cordon.
Length ball, outside off. Siraj swings hard but misses.
Full ball, on off. Ishant Sharma square drives it past the backward point fielder for three runs. Haseeb Hameed gives it a chase and saves a run for his side.
Slower ball, outside off. Mohammed Siraj looks to slog hard but misses.
Overpitched ball, around off. Mohammed Siraj digs it out towards the mid off fielder for a run.
Good-length ball, outside off. Ishant Sharma looks to poke at it but misses.
Full ball, on off. Ishant Sharma drives it straight to the mid off fielder.
Full and straight from Sam Curran. Ishant Sharma squeezes it out to cover.
Good-length ball, on off. Mohammed Siraj taps it towards backward point.
Back of a length, outside off. Siraj stays back to heave it but he misses.
A yorker around middle and leg. Mohammed Siraj squeezes it back to the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT! There it is! What a comeback this has been from the English bowlers. Overton serves a good-length ball, down leg, Siraj makes room on the off side. Siraj looks to cut this one over the slip cordon but he fails to get any elevation and the ball goes towards Joe Root at first slip who jumps to take a good catch. INDIA HAVE BEEN BOWLED OUT FOR 78!
Howout: c Joe Root b Craig Overton

Commentary: Sharma starts with a length ball on the body, Burns nudges this through square leg and takes one. A no ball called as Ishant Sharma oversteps on this occasion.
NO BALL! Length way outside off, Haseeb leaves it. Another no ball from Ishant. Not what his team needs from him now.
On a good length, outside off, Hameed leaves it alone.
WIDE. On a length again, way outside off, Hameed leaves it untouched. The umpire flexes his arms and signals a wide.
FOUR! Haseeb Hameed gets off the mark with a boundary! A very well played shot. Slightly shortish, wider outside off, Haseeb Hameed slaps this one through point and scores a boundary.
Outside off on a length, left alone.
Closer to the off pole on a length, Haseeb shoulders arms.

On a fullish length, around off, Haseeb Hameed looks to drive this one, but the ball takes the inside edge and runs away to the fine leg region. Ravindra Jadeja in the deep runs to his right and dives to stop the ball. The third umpire checks this as they want to ensure if it is a clean stop and replays show that Jadeja has done really well. He saves three for his team and England only get the solitary run.
Length, down the leg side, Rory looks to flick but misses.

STREAKY BOUNDARY! A nervy start for Hameed. Fuller in length, outside off, swinging away, Haseeb Hameed gets low and looks to drive, but the ball takes the outside edge and flies through the gully region to the ropes.
On middle, dropped to the leg side for a run.
Around off, defended out.
Around middle, dropped to the leg side.
Way outside off, Rory makes a leave this time.
Fuller, outside off, Burns shoulders arms.
Length ball, outside off. Haseeb Hameed leaves it alone.
Good-length ball, just outside off, jagging back in. Haseeb Hameed shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length, outside off. Haseeb Hameed lets it go through to the keeper.
Good-length ball, way outside off. Haseeb Hameed hangs back and leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Length ball, angling in on the pads. Haseeb Hameed flicks it through the square leg region for a couple. Cheteshwar Pujara chases the ball and keeps it down to two.
Length ball, way outside off. Haseeb Hameed shoulders arms to it.
Good-length ball, moving away with the angle, outside off. Rory Burns leaves it alone.
Back of a length, down leg. Rory Burns tucks it towards fine leg for a single.
Good-length ball, coming back in, from middle. Haseeb Hameed turns it towards fine leg for a run.
On a length, outside off. Rory Burns shoulders arms to this one.
Length ball, just outside off, moving away with the angle. Rory Burns lets it go to the keeper untouched.
Back of a length, around the fourth stump channel. Rory Burns sways away from the line of the ball.
An inswinger, around off. Haseeb Hameed gets behind the line and blocks it.
Full ball, way outside off. Haseeb Hameed leaves it alone.
Length ball, jagging back in just that little but. Haseeb Hameed prods forward and defends it to cover. They scamper through for a quick run.
Full ball, around the fourth stump. Rory Burns defends it back to the bowler.
Short of a length, down leg. Rory Burns hangs back and turns it towards fine leg for one.
Length ball, angling in from outside off. Haseeb Hameed defends it solidly towards cover and collects a single. Good, sensible batting from these two.
On a length, around off. Haseeb Hameed defends it out off the front foot.
Lovely delivery! Short of a length, outside off, nipping inwards after landing. Haseeb Hameed leaves it alone and the ball zips past his off stump.
Good-length ball, outside off. Haseeb Hameed shoulders arms to it.
Full ball, coming in with the angle. Haseeb Hameed blocks it off the front foot.
Length ball, way outside off. Haseeb Hameed leaves it for the keeper to collect it.
Maiden over! An inswinger, starting from outside off. Haseeb Hameed shoulders arms to it.
Shami starts with a short-of-a-length ball, around off. Rory Burns blocks it off the back foot.
BEAUTY! Great start from Mohammed Shami .Good-length ball, around the fourth stump. Rory Burns looks to defend but is beaten and the ball zips past his outside edge as it straightens after landing.
On a length, around middle. Rory Burns turns it towards mid-wicket.
Good-length ball, around off. Rory Burns taps it towards cover.
Good-length ball, on off. Rory Burns gets behind the line to block this one.
Short of a length, around off. Rory Burns stays back and defends it out solidly. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 1!
Fuller, way outside off, Haseeb shoulders arms.
Similar length, closer to the off pole this time. Haseeb Hameed does not think about playing at this as he leaves.
Good length again, way outside off, Haseeb keeps his wits about himself and watches it go past him.
Fuller, on off, Hameed blocks it out well now.
Angles a length delivery, around off, Haseeb goes back and taps  this to the off side.
Maiden from Bumrah! Around off, nudged to the mid on region.
Outside off on a length, Burns shoulders arms.
Around off, on a length, Burns goes back and nicely guides this past the mid on fielder. Ishant Sharma gives chase and stops the ball, but is not able to stop them from taking three runs.
Around off, length ball, kept out.

That's a beauty from Shami! On a length, around off, Haseeb Hameed looks to defend this with an angled bat, but the ball straightens after hitting the deck, whizzes past the blade, clips the back pad on the way to Pant. Shami appeals but the umpire says no. Kohli gestures that it hit no part of the bat and only the back pad. UltraEdge confirms the same.
On middle, flicked to square leg.
On off, defended out.
On the body, Rory looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the body.
Fuller on middle and leg, Rory misses his clip and the ball takes the pad and goes to Pant.
On a length, closer to the off pole, Rory does not bother playing at this.
Good length, on middle and leg, rises after the ball pitches, Rory looks to flick but misses again.
Around middle, this is glanced past Rahane at leg slip, for a single.
Around off on a length, Haseeb defends it well.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Around off, dabbed to the gully fielder.
Outside off on a length, Rory leaves it.
FOUR! Lovely. Burns made it look so easy. There was no point chasing after this as this one was racing away to the ropes. On a length, outside off, Rory Burns leans and creams this through covers.
This is defended to the leg side.
On middle, length, clipped straight to the square leg fielder.
Around off, defended well.
Good length on off, Haseeb defends it with the full face of the blade.
An action replay of the previous delivery.
Fullish and sliding down the leg side, HH misses his clip away.
Outside off, length delivery, Haseeb shoulders arms.
Arrows in a length delivery on off, Hameed pushes it to covers now.
Short of a length, outside off, dabbed towards point.

Could have been a run out there, but Burns survives. Around off, this is tapped to point and Rory Burns is off, looking for a run, but Haseeb Hameed sends him back. Cheteshwar Pujara runs ahead, collects the ball and has a shy at the striker's end but misses.
A couple as this is stroked past the mid off fielder.
Good length outside off, pushed behind point for a quick single.

FOUR! Beautiful shot. Hameed is looking more and more composed, as time passes by. Lovely balance as well. Fuller in length, around off and middle, Haseeb Hameed goes back and whips this delightfully through mid-wicket.
On off, kept out nicely.
Back of a length this time, around off, it rises steeply this time as Burns moves away. The ball takes his shoulder and goes to the slip cordon.
Short this time, on the body, Rory is quick to sit under this one.
Length outside off, Burns gets an inside edge onto his pad.
Outside off, length, this is guided to the man at gully.
Fuller this time, wider too, no reason for Rory to play at this and he leaves.
Down the leg side, Rory misses his flick this time. Pant shuffles quickly and collects the ball.
Shami bends his back and hurls a short ball outside off, Hameed just sways away from the line of the ball.
Short of a length, around off, punched to point.
Quick single! Around off, length ball, pushed away to the cover region for one.
Pushed to the fielder at covers this time.
Around off, defended watchfully under his eyes.
Outside off, pushed to the point region.
On a length, around off. Haseeb Hameed prods forward to defend this one out.
Full ball, angling in from middle. Haseeb Hameed turns it towards mid on.
Back of a length, around off. Haseeb Hameed taps it behind square on the off side.
BEATEN! Good-length ball, outside off. Haseeb Hameed looks to poke at it but is beaten as the ball zips past his outside edge.
Length ball, around off. Haseeb Hameed blocks it off the front foot.
A slower ball, on a length, on off. Haseeb Hameed gets deceived, but digs it out back to the bowler, in time.
Full ball, jagging back in from middle. Rory Burns turns it towards square leg.
BEATEN! Length ball, outside off, moving away after pitching. Rory Burns looks to drive on the up but misses.
BEAUTY! Good-length ball, just outside off. Rory Burns looks to defend but the ball nips away slightly after landing and beats his outside edge.
Back of a length, on middle. Rory Burns turns it towards mid-wicket.
Length ball, angling in from outside off. Rory Burns looks to defend but gets an outside edge and the ball rolls away towards the slip cordon.
Back of a length, on off. Rory Burns looks to defend but misses as there is some extra bounce and Rory Burns gets hit high on his pads.
Full ball, way outside off. Haseeb Hameed leaves it alone.
Another ball, sprayed way outside off. Haseeb Hameed shoulders arms to it.
FOUR! SMASHED! Short and wide. Haseeb Hameed stays back and cuts it hard through backward point for a boundary. The fielder at point is unmoved and the ball races away.
FOUR! AND AGAIN! Short ball, outside off. Haseeb Hameed rocks back and cuts it back past the point fielder for a boundary.
Length ball, jagging back from off. Haseeb Hameed defends it off the front foot.
An inswinger from Ishant, around the off pole. Haseeb Hameed comes forward and blocks it solidly.
Short of a length, around off. Rory Burns punches it off the back foot to mid off.
A tad short, outside off. Rory Burns stays back and cuts it straight to Ravindra Jadeja at backward point.
Length ball, around middle. Rory Burns defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, on off. Rory Burns rocks back and turns it wide of the mid on fielder for a single.
Good-length ball, coming back in from off. Haseeb Hameed blocks it off the back foot.
Length ball, just outside off. Haseeb Hameed comes forward to block this one out.
Good-length ball, angling in from off. Rory Burns defends it off the back foot.
Ishant spills one down leg. Rory Burns misses the flick and the ball goes to Rishabh Pant behind the sticks who dives to his right to collect it.
Good-length ball, on off. Rory Burns defends it back to the bowler.
Short of a length, on middle and leg. Rory Burns stays back and works it wide of the fine leg fielder for a couple.
Length ball, strayed on the pads. Rory Burns misses the flick and the ball clips his pads before going to Rishabh Pant behind the stumps.
Full ball, on middle. Rory Burns flicks it towards mid-wicket, where Ravindra Jadeja dives to his right to stop the ball.
Good-length ball, on off. Haseeb Hameed blocks it off the front foot.
Length ball, coming in from outside off. Haseeb Hameed leaves it alone.
Length ball, jagging back in from off. Haseeb Hameed gets behind the line to block it out.

FOUR! Nicely played! Short and wide. Haseeb Hameed stays back and cuts it hard through the cover region for a boundary. Also brings up the 50-run stand between these two. England have struggled to get a good partnership in this series and their openers have provided the platform for them here.
Good-length ball, on off. Haseeb Hameed defends it off the front foot.
Length ball, around the fourth stump channel. Haseeb Hameed defends it solidly off the front foot.
Length ball, strayed on the pads. Rory Burns whips it off his pads towards fine leg for a single.
Length ball, way outside off. Haseeb Hameed shoulders arms to this one.
Good-length ball, on off. Haseeb Hameed blocks it off the front foot.
Length ball, around off. Haseeb Hameed gets behind the line and defends it solidly.
Length ball, way outside off. Haseeb Hameed lets it go through to the keeper.
Full ball, just outside off. Haseeb Hameed whips it off his pads towards the mid on fielder. Haseeb Hameed would feel that he missed out to score on such a loose ball.
FOUR! SMASHED! Tossed up, outside off. Rory Burns gets low and slog-sweeps it towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Flatter ball, on off. Rory Burns punches it back to the bowler.
Tossed up, around off, Rory Burns blocks it out.
Tossed up, outside off. Rory Burns defends it off the front foot.
Flighted ball, around middle. Rory Burns steps out and works it down towards mid on for a single.
Flighted ball, on off. Haseeb Hameed defends it off the front foot.
Length ball, on off. Rory Burns defends it to mid off.
Short of a length, around off. Rory Burns blocks it off the back foot.
Back of a length, on off. Rory Burns blocks it off the back foot.
Good-length ball, on off. Rory Burns stays back and defends it back to the bowler.
Good-length ball, outside off. Rory Burns blocks it out towards the off side.
FOUR! CLASSY! Full ball, just outside off. Rory Burns drives it through mid off for a boundary. Ishant Sharma at mid off dives to his left but the ball goes past him.
Around off. Haseeb Hameed taps it towards point.
Flatter ball, on off. Haseeb Hameed blocks it off the back foot.
Around off. Haseeb Hameed stays back and cuts it to cover.
Tossed up, on off. Haseeb Hameed blocks it off the front foot.
Flatter ball, outside off. Haseeb Hameed pushes it to cover.
Quicker ball, around middle and leg. Haseeb Hameed blocks it out solidly.
Good length around off, Burns taps this to the leg side.
Around off, on a length, Burns looks to push but gets an inside edge, back onto the pad.
Fuller, outside off, Burns looks to defend but gets beaten as the ball shapes away very late.

Good work by the duo of Ravindra Jadeja and Ishant Sharma this time. Both combine well and save a run for their side. On a length, around off, this is flicked wonderfully through mid-wicket. Jadeja chases after this. Sharma chases after Jadeja, as RJ pulls the ball back and Sharma throws it back into the middle. Three runs. Mohammed Siraj oversteps and so, a no ball is called.
Around off, tapped to point.
Angles a length ball, around off, Haseeb defends it out.
Outside off, this is pushed hard towards the mid off fielder.
Slower through the air, around off, Rory pushes this to point.
Quicker, on off, Burns defends.
A touch shortish, around off, Burns nudges this to the square leg fielder.

FOUR BYES! Turn and bounce on this one. Tosses this one up, lands it around off, the ball hits the deck and spins in, as Rory Burns looks to drive but gets beaten easily. The turn takes Rishabh by surprise too and he misses as the ball runs away to the ropes.
Burns plays this one through the cover region for a single.
Around off, pushed to the mid off fielder this time.
Pitches it up and outside off, this is driven crisply to the left of the mid off fielder.

SIX! Ohhhh! What a shot. Not everyday that you see Burns hitting a six, but this time, he connects it well. On a shortish length, around off and middle, Rory Burns powers this one over the fielder at deep square leg for a biggie. England behind by just 1 run!
Scores level! Short, on off, pulled to deep square leg again for one.
Hameed gets behind the line of the ball and blocks well.
Around off, pushed to the off side.
Length around off, Hameed works it to the mid off region.
Slower, loopy, outside off, tapped to point.
On middle, pushed back to Jadeja.
Short, on middle, nudged to the leg side.
Floated, fuller on off, tucked to the short mid-wicket fielder.
Floated, on off, Rory prods forward and blocks well.
Again, Burns goes back and taps this to the square leg fielder.
Around off, kept out.
A pacier full ball around off, Hameed gets his bat down and nudges this to the leg side.
Back of a length, angling inwards, on middle and leg, Haseeb looks to work this to the leg side but misses and gets hit on the body.
Siraj dishes a spicy bouncer on the body, Hameed is taken by surprise as he swivels and leaves it, in the end.
Back of a length, on off, defended out.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Flatter, on off, RB dabs it to point.
Around off and middle, played towards mid-wicket.
Given air this time, landing fuller outside off, Burns looks to drive but only manages an inside edge back onto the pad.
Just a mere push to the man at gully.
Burns gently blocks this one out to the off side.
A carbon copy of the previous delivery.
Shami starts another spell with a short-of-a-length delivery around off, Rory goes back and defends it out to the leg side.
Outside off, pushed away from the body, to the point region.

FOUR! Stop the press. There is a fumble in the field from Ravindra Jadeja! It is not everyday that you see the southpaw make an error out on the field. You would think that he would stop the ball 99 times out of 100, but this is that one time. A short ball, outside off, Haseeb Hameed rides the bounce and crunches this through point. Ravindra Jadeja runs to his right, but the ball sneaks underneath his hand and runs away to the ropes.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
EDGED AND FOUR! A length ball, around off, Haseeb Hameed looks to defend, but the ball takes the outside edge and runs away past the slip cordon, to the third man fence.
Around off, worked to the mid on region.
Fuller, outside off, Burns leaves.
Pushed away gently to the mid on fielder.
Length on off, kept out.
Outside off on a length, pushed to mid off.
Outside off, length ball, driven past the point fielder for a run.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Back of a length, on off. Rory Burns blocks it off the back foot.
Good-length ball, around middle. Rory Burns turns it towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Nicely done! A tad short, outside off. Rory Burns stays back and cuts it past the backward point fielder for a boundary!
Length ball, around off. Rory Burns pushes it to mid off.
Short of a length, outside off. Rory Burns leaves it alone watchfully.
Short of a length, around off. Rory Burns looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge towards deep backward point for a couple.
Good-length ball, on off. Haseeb Hameed blocks it out.
Full ball, outside off. Haseeb Hameed defends it off the front foot.
Full ball, darted on the pads. Haseeb Hameed clips it off his pads towards deep mid-wicket for a couple.
Good-length ball, around off. Haseeb Hameed defends it off the front foot.
Short of a length, on middle. Haseeb Hameed blocks it out nicely.
Good-length ball, around off. Haseeb Hameed taps it in front of the wicket with soft hands.
Length ball, around off. Rory Burns pushes it to mid off.
Banged in short, down leg. Rory Burns ducks under it.
Short of a length, on middle and leg. Rory Burns turns it towards square leg for a single.
Good-length ball, on off. Haseeb Hameed defends it to cover.
FOUR! SHOT! A tad short, outside off. Haseeb Hameed waits for it and cuts this one late back past the slip cordon for a boundary!
Short of a length, on middle and leg. Haseeb Hameed works it on the leg side for a single.
Length ball, angling in from off. Haseeb Hameed blocks it out.

FOUR! EDGED AND DROPPED! Haseeb Hameed brings up his FIFTY! Length ball, outside off. Haseeb Hameed pokes at it and gets an outside edge towards Rohit Sharma at second slip who moves to his left with one hand but drops it and the ball races away towards the boundary ropes.
Length ball, outside off. Haseeb Hameed defends it out.
Back of a length, outside off. Haseeb Hameed leaves it alone.
Length ball, on off. Haseeb Hameed defends it off the front foot.
Good-length ball, around off. Haseeb Hameed taps it to cover.
Back of a length, on middle. Rory Burns turns it towards mid-wicket.
Short of a length, on off. Rory Burns stays back and pushes it to cover.
Good-length ball, angling in from off. Rory Burns defends it off the front foot.
Length ball, strayed on the pads. Rory Burns whips it off his pads towards square leg for a single.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Haseeb Hameed works it behind square on the leg side for a run.
Good-length ball, around off. Rory Burns taps it towards the cover fielder.
Length ball, way outside off. Haseeb Hameed leaves it alone.
Back of a length, outside off, angling in late. Haseeb Hameed shoulders arms to it.
Overpitched ball, outside off. Haseeb Hameed digs it out to cover.
Short of a length, around off. Haseeb Hameed blocks it off the back foot.
Length ball, angling in with the angle, around off. Haseeb Hameed defends it off the front foot.
Good-length ball, jagging back in from middle. Haseeb Hameed works it behind square on the leg side for one.
Shami goes wide of the crease and strays one on the pads. Haseeb Hameed flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
Full ball, coming in with the angle, from off. Rory Burns pushes it back to the bowler.
An appeal for LBW but the umpire turns it down. Good-length ball, angling in from middle. Rory Burns looks to defend but misses and gets hit high on his pad.
A tad short, outside off. Rory Burns cuts it towards sweeper cover for one.
Length ball, jagging back in. Haseeb Hameed defends it off the front foot.
Good-length ball, angling in late, around off. Haseeb Hameed pushes it to mid on off the front foot.
Length ball, around off. Rory Burns drives it towards the mid off fielder.
Good-length ball, on middle. Rory Burns works it towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Length ball, nipping away after landing, from off. Rory Burns defends it solidly off the front foot.

FOUR! Nicely played! Rory Burns brings up his FIFTY in style. Length ball, on middle. Rory Burns flicks it off his pads through the mid-wicket region for a boundary. Ishant Sharma gives it a chase but the ball wins easily in the end.
Overpitched ball, outside off. Rory Burns looks to dig it out but misses.
Length ball, around off. Rory Burns blocks it out solidly.
Good-length ball, on off. Haseeb Hameed taps it towards the backward point fielder.
Length ball, just outside off. Haseeb Hameed prods forward and defends it to cover.
FOUR! Cleverly done! Good-length ball, outside off. Haseeb Hameed hangs back and bisects the first and second slip to perfection. The ball races away for a boundary.
Length ball, on off. Haseeb Hameed defends it back to the bowler.
Full ball, way outside off. Haseeb Hameed leaves it alone.

Length ball, strayed on the pads. Haseeb Hameed misses the flick and gets rapped on the pads, to the naked eye. Mohammed Siraj appeals but the umpire is unmoved. The ball rolls away towards square leg and they take a run. The fielder at square leg has a shy at the striker's end but he misses and they run one more. Virat Kohli thinks to opt for a review but decides to not take it in the end. The umpires do not give these runs as leg byes, and so, perhaps there was bat on this. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 1!
Ishant starts from 'round the wicket, with a length ball, down leg. Burns stays back and flicks it towards fine leg. The fielder comes in and keeps it down to just one.
Good-length ball, wide outside off. Hameed leaves it alone.
On a length, on the fifth stump line. Hameed shoulders his arms.
CLOSE! This was better from Sharma, A length ball, just outside off. Hameed prods and leaves it alone.
Good variations by Sharma. He bangs this one short, outside off. Hameed sways away from the delivery.
Good-length ball and outside off. Hameed leaves it alone for the keeper.
Shami starts 'round the wicket with a short one, on middle. Burns ducks under it.
On a length, around  off. Burns stays back and defends it out watchfully.
Shami angles in a full delivery, on off. Burns hangs back and defends it out to the off side.
A length ball, on off. Burns rocks back and offers a straight bat to defend it out to mid on.
Full and on middle. Burns blocks it to mid-wicket.
On a length, outside off. This one comes back in. Burns shoulders his arms.
Back-of-a-length ball, outside off. Hameed just watches it go past him to the keeper.
A full-length ball, on off. Hameed pushes it to cover and takes off for a single.
Looks like Sharma is still finding his line. On a length, sliding down leg. Burns looks to flick it away but misses. Pant moves to his right to collect it comfortably.
A length ball, on off. Burns defends it out solidly.
FOUR! Nicely played. The first boundary of the day comes from Burns. Sharma serves it full and on the pads. Burns hangs back and clips it through square leg. The ball races away to the boundary.
Full-length ball, around off. Burns stays back and defends it out watchfully.
Good length and just outside off. Hameed has no stroke to offer.
On a length, outside off. Hameed lets it go to the keeper.

FOUR! Hameed takes the charge now. A full-length ball, on the pads. The ball comes straight off the deck. Hameed clips it through square leg and the ball races away to the boundary. This pair is continuing from where it left off last evening.
Back-of-a-length ball and on off. Hameed stays back and defends it out.
Good length and outside off. Hameed leaves it alone.
A sharp bouncer now, on off. Hameed ducks under it.
Sharma serves it full and on off. Burns blocks it out watchfully.
On a length, outside off. Burns shoulders his arms.
Full and on leg. Burns stays back and nudges it to mid-wicket.

Full-length ball, on leg. Burns stays back and flicks it through mid-wicket. The ball goes through the gap. Mohammed Siraj comes running in from the deep and puts in a diving effort to save the ball from going into the boundary. The batters take three.
A length ball, on off. Hameed prods and defends it out.
Much better from Ishant Sharma. A full-length ball, on off. Hameed is cramped for space. He defends it to cover.
On a length and on the pads. Burns stays back and defends it to the leg side.
A full-length ball, on middle and leg. Burns tucks it to the leg side.
A length delivery, on off. Burns defends it out watchfully.
Shami serves a good-length ball, on off. Burns defends it back to the bowler.
The pitch is not offering anything to the bowlers at the moment. Shami bowls it full and on off. Burns defends it out with ease.
A length ball, on off. Burns stays inside the crease and defends it out solidly.
A full-length ball, just outside off. Hameed stays back and pushes it to cover.

There was a noise. But that was not an outside edge. Wonder where the noise came from? On a length and just outside off. Hameed looks to defend it out but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge. Kohli and Pant had already started the celebration but they could not continue.
Full and on off. Hameed blocks it to the right of gully. The batters take a quick single.
Sharma serves it full and on the pads. Burns clips it to deep square leg for another single.
On a length and on off. Hameed stays back and blocks it onto the pitch.
A length ball, on off. Hameed defends it out solidly.
Full and on off. Burns tucks it to the leg side.
A length ball, on middle. Burns defends it out solidly.
Shami serves a full-length ball, on off. Burns defends it to mid off.
Good length and on off. Burns looks to defend it out. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards gully. This is what India need to do to get the edge into play.
A length ball, on off. Burns defends it out watchfully.

OUT! TIMBER! That's the one Shami was looking for. He finds the breakthrough that India were hunting for so while. The Birthday Boy could not gift himself a ton, he will be disappointed. But he surely has given his team a dream start after a long, long time. Shami serves it full and around off. The ball nips in a bit. Burns looks to defend it out but gets beaten. The ball goes through the gap between bat and pad. The ball comes in contact with the off stump. Some delight in the Indian camp finally.
Howout: b Mohammed Shami

Commentary: Bumrah starts with a fuller length, on the off pole. Haseeb Hameed defends it off the front foot towards covers.
Good-length delivery, angling in on off. Hameed blocks it under his eyes.
Good-length ball, in the trajectory of uncertainty. Hameed leaves it untouched.
Big movement there! Good-length ball, nipping back in, around off. Haseeb Hameed watches the ball closely and makes a good leave.
Fuller in length this time, on off. Hameed pushes it back to the bowler.
Single off the last ball! Length ball on middle, Hameed tucks it towards square leg. He keeps the strike by picking up a single.
Full and on off, Hameed lunges forward and drives it but finds the cover fielder.
Good-length ball on off, Hameed is solid in his defense.
Full again on off, angling in from wide of the crease. Hameed watchfully blocks it out.
Fuller in length on off, Hameed blocks it off the front foot.
Shami continue to bowl full on off, Hameed pushes it to silly mid off.
Length ball on off, Hameed defends it down onto the deck. A maiden from Shami.
Bumrah serves a full ball, around off. Malan drives it towards extra cover.
Good-length ball on middle, Malan pats the ball gently down the ground.
Good-length ball from Bumrah, angling away, outside off. Malan shoulders arms to that one.
Back of a length, on middle. Malan hops and taps it on the off side.
FOUR! Malan is off the mark! Length ball outside off, Dawid Malan puts a stride forward, opens the face of the bat, and creams it through covers for a boundary.
Bumrah comes 'round the wicket, pitches it on a length, outside off. Dawid Malan lets it sail through.
Good-length ball on off, Hameed blocks the ball right under his eyes.
Length ball on off, Hameed stays solid in his defense.
Short ball around off, Hameed takes his eyes off the ball and sways away from it.
Fuller in length, on middle. Hameed flicks it to behind square for a run.
Good-length ball on off, angling in. Malan taps it towards point.

That's the one Shami is targeting! Get Malan to drive! This one was a full ball, around off. Dawid Malan goes for an expansive drive but fails to get any bat to it. The ball fizzes past the inside edge.
Edged but did not carry! Good-length ball outside off, Hameed looks to defend but gets an outside edge. The ball goes towards the slip cordon.
Back of a length, on off. Hameed watchfully blocks it out.
An effort ball from Bumrah, outside off. Hameed sways away from it.
Length delivery, on the sixth-stump channel, Hameed leaves it for the keeper to collect.
A low full toss on middle, Hameed looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball rolls back to the bowler.
Length ball, on middle, angling in. Hameed comes forward and pushes it to mid on.
Back of a length, on off. Malan dabs it towards the slip cordon.
Back of a length again, outside off, Malan lets it sail through.
On a length, around off, Malan stays on the back foot and shoulders arms.
Length ball outside off, jagging back in. Malan leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Good-length ball on off, Malan defends it down the ground.
A touch fuller this time, around off. Malan pushes it towards covers.
Back of a length and just outside off. Hameed ducks under it.
Quicker delivery! On a length and outside off. The ball gets an extra bounce off the pitch. Hameed looks to defend it out but pulls his bat back in time. The ball zips past the outside edge.
A length ball, on off. Hameed stays back and defends it out off the outer half to backward point.
A sharp bouncer, on off. Hameed ducks under it.
Back of a length and outside off. Hameed ducks under this one and leaves it alone.
Good-length ball, outside off. Hameed watches it sail past him.

FOUR! Malan puts the pressure straightaway on the new bowler. Back of a length and on the fourth stump line. Malan stays back and cuts it through point. The ball races away to the boundary. Not the welcome Siraj wanted.
A length ball, on off. Malan defends it to cover.

FOUR! Second one in the over. You offer width to Malan and he will make sure he punishes. A touch short and outside off. Malan hangs back and cuts it away. The ball races away to the boundary at third man.
On a length and outside off. Malan shoulders his arms.
Good-length ball, outside off, moving away a bit. Malan lets it go to the keeper.
Siraj serves it on a length and on off. Malan defends it out watchfully.
A length ball, on off. Hameed defends it back to the bowler off the front foot.

OUCH! This one is on the helmet. That must've hurt a little bit. A touch short and on off. Hameed thought the ball will bounce over him and he ducks under it. But the ball does not get the bounce, as he anticipated it to be. The ball goes onto hit his helmet and go towards the leg side.

A loud appeal for LBW but turned down. A length ball, pitching around off. The ball nips in. Hameed stays back and looks to flick it away but misses. He gets rapped on his pads. Bumrah puts in a appeal but the umpire says no. Maybe, it was angling down the leg side.
Outside off, left alone.
A length ball, on off. Hameed defends it watchfully.
Tentative attempt by Hameed. On a length and outside off. Hameed looks to have a poke at it but misses. The ball beats the outside edge.
Good-length ball, outside off, moving away from the left-hander. Malan leaves it alone for the keeper.
Siraj serves it on a length and on off. Malan defends it to cover.
A length ball, outside off. The ball nips away off the pitch. Malan has no stroke to offer.
A length ball, on off. Malan defends it out solidly.

FOUR LEG BYES! Freebies and England wouldn't mind it. Full and down leg. Malan stays back and looks to flick it away but misses. The ball clips the pads and goes towards fine leg. It ends up in the boundary and the umpire signals leg byes.
Full and on off, Malan pushes it to cover.
Good-length ball on off, Hameed prods and looks to defend it with soft hands. The ball goes off the outside edge towards gullly.
Good-length delivery, outside off, 138 kph, Hameed lets it sail through.
Bumrah bangs a short ball on off, Hameed sits under it. Rishabh Pant jumps and carries it over his head.
Length ball on middle, blocked out off the front foot.
On a length, on middle. Hameed nudges it to mid-wicket.
Another short ball from Bumrah, on middle. Hameed ducks underneath.
Back of a length, on middle. Malan stands tall and pushes it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Nicely played! Width on offer outside off, Malan pounces on it and steers it through point for a boundary. A confident-looking shot from Malan.
Back of a length, on off. Malan taps it towards point and gets a single.
Length ball on off, Hameed puts a stride forward before blocking it out.
Siraj bangs a bumper, on middle. Haseeb Hameed sways away from it.
On middle, Hameed nudges it on the leg side with ease.
Flatter ball on off, Dawid Malan steps out and looks to defend but gets hit on the pads.
Flatter ball outside off, Malan blocks it out with his pads.
Full and on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Flatter ball on middle, Malan clips it towards square leg for a single.
Loopy ball on off, Hameed blocks it right under his eyes.

OUT! TIMBER! Ravindra Jadeja gets his first wicket of the series! What a time to get the breakthrough! Jadeja bowls a loopy ball around off, Haseeb Hameed puts a big stride forward. He looks to defend but the ball turns just enough to get past his willow. Hameed misses out and the ball crashes the top of the off pole. Hameed was looking very good but has to depart. He is disappointed. Jubilation for India and dejection for Haseeb Hameed.
Howout: b Ravindra Jadeja

Commentary: Good-length ball on off, angling in. Malan looks to defend but misses. He gets hit on the back pad and the ball goes towards the slip cordon. An appeal from India for a caught behind but nothing from the umpire.

Full and on off, Malan blocks it out on the off side. Mohammed Siraj picks up the ball and throws it at the ball at the striker's end but misses. The ball races away to the boundary as there is no one backing up. Not sure why Siraj threw the ball though because Malan was well in.
Back of a length, on off. Malan defends it towards covers.
On a length, outside off. Malan dabs it to gully.
Back of a length on off, Malan pushes it to mid on.
On a length on middle, Malan works it on the leg side for a single.
Flatter one on off, Malan defends it out.
Floated it up outside off, Malan is solid in his defense.
Full and outside off, Malan pushes it to cover for a single.
Off the mark straightaway! Short and on off, Root hangs back and punches it towards point for one.
Flatter, full and on off. Malan pushes it to mid on for a quick single.
Flatter and quicker on middle and leg, Root glances it towards deep square leg for a couple of runs.
On a length, around off. Malan taps it towards covers.
Good-length delivery, around off, nipping in. Malan lets it sail through.
Length ball on middle, Malan defends it to mid on.
Fuller in length, on off. Malan tries to drive but misses and gets beaten on the inside edge.

A mix-up but no harm done! On a length on off, Malan taps it towards backward point. He calls for a single and is halfway down the track. But Root says no. In the end, he goes for it and makes it to the other end comfortably as Ajinkya Rahane fumbles to collect the ball quickly.
A yorker on off, Root negotiates with it safely enough.

Short and outside off, Malan rocks back and punches it towards backward point. Mohammed Siraj does well to dive to his left and stop the ball. Gave away four earlier with overthrows but saves a boundary now. A single taken.
Flatter ball on leg, Root blocks it out.
Loopy ball on off, driven towards covers.
Floated it up on off, Root pushes it on the off side.
On middle, Root nudges it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Flatter ball on off, Root steers it towards covers for a quick single.
Good-length ball, on off, nipping back in. Root looks to defend but misses. He gets hit on the thigh pad.
FOUR! Deft touch! On a length, outside off. Joe Root plays it late and guides it past Rohit Sharma at second slip for a boundary.
Length ball on off, Root pushes it to mid on.
FOUR! Again in the same area! Good-length ball outside off, Joe Root rocks back and cuts it late past the second and third slip for a boundary. England lead by 104 runs now!
On a length, on off, nipping in. Root blocks it out from the crease.
A touch fuller on middle, Root defends it well to mid on. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 2.
Jadeja starts with a flighted delivery, full and on off. Malan defends it back to the bowler.
Short and around off. Malan stays back and guides it towards point.
Full and on off. Malan pushes it back to the bowler.
Some turn for Jadeja now. Loopy ball, outside off. The ball turns in. Malan prods and looks to drive it away but misses, he gets beaten by the turn there.
On off, Malan goes back and defends it out.
Tossed up, on off. Malan defends it out watchfully.

A full-length ball, around off. Root takes a step forward, he waits for the ball and guides it towards third man. They take one. And the crowd gets into the action as well with a huge roar 'ROOT', for the English skipper.
A length ball, on the pads. Malan stays back and tucks it to square leg for another single.
A length ball, around off. Root stays inside the crease and defends it to point.
On a length and around off. Root hangs back and punches it towards point. But straight to the fielder.
A length ball, on the stumps. Root hangs back and defends it onto the pitch.
Full length and on off. Root pushes it past mid off. The ball races away but Jadeja is quick enough to cut it off. The batters take three.
Tossed up, on middle and off. Root prods and blocks it out.
Darted on the pads. Root tucks it to short leg.
Floated full and on off. Root defends it with a straight bat.
FOUR! Freebies. Full toss and on leg. Root comes forward and whips it through mid-wicket. Rohit Sharma puts in a diving effort but the ball goes past him. The ball races away to the boundary.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries. A touch short, on middle. Root goes back and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Loopy ball, on off. Root pushes it to cover and takes off for a single.
Good-length ball on off, Root punches it towards covers.
A touch fuller this time, on off. Root drives it towards covers.
Length ball on middle, Root nudges it to mid on.
Length ball, outside off, Root lets it be.
Good-length ball, on off. Root taps it towards covers.
Good-length ball, well outside off, Root rocks back and cuts it towards deep point. He retains the strike by taking a single.
Tossed up and on off. Root defends it on the off side.
Floated full and on off. Root blocks it back to the bowler.
Flighted and on the pads. Root goes back and flicks it to the leg side.
Short and on off. Root hangs back and taps it to point. They take one.
Some turn on this one. Loopy ball, outside off. The ball turns in off the pitch. Malan looks to defend it out but misses and gets rapped on the pads.
Full and on off. Malan blocks it out watchfully.
FOUR! In the gap! A length ball, on off. Root stays back and punches it through cover. The ball races away to the boundary. He looks like a man on a mission. The crowd cheers with a loud ROO.
Outside off, Root leaves it alone.
A full-length ball, on off. Root gets squared up. The ball goes off the outside edge through point. The batters take a couple. Good running.
A length ball, on off. Root defends it out solidly.

A full-length ball, outside off. Root goes for the booming drive and connects it well. The ball goes towards cover. But Jadeja is up to the task. He dives to his right and makes an excellent stop to save a boundary.
Full and on off. Root defends it to cover.
FOUR BYES! Floated full and just outside off. Malan looks to push it to the off side but misses. The ball goes through the keeper's legs. It races away to the boundary. The umpire signals it as byes.
Full and outside off. Malan misses his attempted drive. Pant this time shuts the gap between his gloves and his legs and the ball does not sneak through this time.
Outside off, left alone.
Tossed up, on off. Malan flicks it through mid-wicket and takes off for a single. The stand moves to 50.
Full and on off. Root prods and defends it to silly point.
Darted on the pads. Root flicks it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length, on middle. Malan pats it back to the bowler.
Good-length ball, outside off. Malan shoulders arms.
Ohh! Good-length delivery, around off, shaping away a bit. Malan looks to defend it off the front foot but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge and carries through to the keeper.
On a length, on middle. Malan tucks it towards square leg for a run.
Back of a length, on off. Root stands tall and punches it back to the bowler.
Good-length ball on off, angling in. Root knocks it towards mid on.
Flatter ball on off, Malan blocks it out.
Full and on leg, pushed to silly mid on.
Flatter and quicker on middle, Malan is solid in his defense.
Full and on leg, worked to silly mid on.
FOUR! Well played! Short and outside off, Dawid Malan sees the width, takes full advantage of it and cuts it through point for a boundary.
Floated it up on off, Malan prods and defends it on the off side.
Good-length ball on middle, Root defends it down onto the pitch with a dead bat.
Length ball on leg, Root clips it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
A touch fuller from Siraj, on middle. Malan watchfully blocks it out.
On a length, on off. Malan taps it towards covers.
Back of a length, on middle. Malan defends it back to the bowler.
Short of a length, on middle. Malan pulls it towards mid-wicket.
Full and on off, Root drives it towards deep cover for one.
Loopy ball on off, Malan knocks it back to the bowler.
A low full toss on leg, Malan works it to mid on for a run.
FOUR! This is a Root masterclass! Flatter ball on middle, Joe Root is aware there is not much turn and he sweeps it towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary. Flawless shot.
On middle, blocked out.
Full and on middle, Root digs it out to mid on.
Short ball on middle, Malan sways away from it.
Short of a length, outside off. Malan dabs it towards deep backward point for a run.
On a length, on off. Root defends it towards covers.
Short of a length, outside off. Root guides it towards deep backward point. He calls for the second run and gets it comfortably. Excellent running between the wickets.
Length ball on middle, Root nudges it to mid-wicket.

Fuller length, outside off. Joe Root drives it towards deep point for a single. The fielder from the deep has a wild throw at the keeper's end. The throws was well over Pant and there is no one backing up. The batters take a single off the overthrows. Mohammed Siraj is clearly not happy with that.
Full toss and on off. Malan defends it out to cover. There was some swing on it.
Good-length ball and outside off. The ball nips away off the pitch. Malan watches it sail past him.
Bumrah fires in a full length ball, on the pads. Malan tucks it to the left of mid on.
On a length and outside off. This one comes back in. Malan stays back and swings his bat. The ball goes towards cover.
Well bowled! On a length. This one comes back in from outside off. Malan shoulders his arms.
FOUR! Sheer timing on that one. A full-length ball, on off. Malan leans on and creams it through the cover region for a boundary.
Full length ball, on the pads. Root flicks it through square leg for a couple.

FOUR! Root just keeps scoring runs. He has been the best batsman in this series. He gets his FIFTY in some style. A touch short, on off. Root stays back, hops and punches it through the point region for a boundary.
A length ball, on the pads. Root flicks it through square leg for a couple.
A length ball, on off. Root looks to defend it out. The ball goes towards square leg off the inner half. They take one.
A length ball, on off. Malan defends it out solidly.
Good length and outside off. Malan lets it go to the keeper.
On a length and around off. Root defends it to the off side.
A length ball, on off. Root works it towards backward point for a single.
Full and on the pads. Malan flicks it to mid-wicket and takes off for a single.
BEAUTY! Good-length ball and on the fourth stump line. Root looks to defends it out but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge. The umpire signals a no ball, as the bowler oversteps.
A length ball, around off. Root plays it late and guides it towards third man for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Malan leaves it alone for the keeper.
Bumrah fires a yorker, on off. Malan digs it out back to the bowler.
A length ball, on off. Root defends it to backward point for a single.

FOUR! Just a sweet touch this time. A length ball, around off. Malan stays back and he plays late at it. He opens the face of the bat and guides it past gully. The ball races away to the boundary at third man.
FOUR! Nailed it. Two in a row. A touch short and outside off. Malan stays back and hammers it through point. The ball races away to the boundary. Malan moves to 49.
Length ball on off, Malan nudges it to mid on.
Length ball on leg, Malan blocks it out.
Shami angles in a full-length ball, on off. Malan blocks it out.
Bumrah serves a full-length ball, on off. Root pushes it to mid off.
FOUR! The runs just keep coming for England. Trademark shot from Joe Root. A touch short and on off. Root stays back and plays the back foot punch. The ball goes through point for a boundary.
Good-length ball, just outside off. Root shoulders his arms.
On a length, outside off. The ball nips in off the pitch. Root prods and defends it out.
A length ball, on off. Root pushes it to cover.
Full-length ball, on off. Root hangs back and defends it out watchfully.
Shami bangs in a short ball, on middle. Dawid Malan ducks underneath.

Edged but does not carry! Good-length ball around off, Dawid Malan looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes towards the keeper but falls short. Dawid Malan need to be careful batting at 49.

FIFTY! What a comeback innings it has been from Dawid Malan! The crowd is up on its feet and he gets an applause from his teammates as well. This was on a length, on off. Malan guides it to third man for a single. Joe Root comes up to him to congratulate as well.
Full and on off, Root drives it to extra cover for a run.
Length ball on the pads, Malan glances it towards deep square leg for a single. 100-run partnership comes up between Malan and Root. Both the batters give each other a fist bump.
Fuller in length, outside off. Root drives it to mid off.
Length ball, well outside off. Malan leaves it for the keeper to collect. Ishant Sharma has overstepped and will have to reload again. No Ball signalled by the umpire.
Good-length ball, outside off. Malan watches the ball closely and lets it be.
FOUR! Deft touch! On a length around off, Dawid Malan stays deep in the crease and dabs it towards third man for a boundary. Runs are coming pretty thick and fast for England.
A single this time! Outside off, Malan guides it to deep backward point for one.
Fuller in length, on off. Root puts a stride forward and pushes it back to the bowler. Another No Ball as Ishant oversteps.
Full on off, Root hits it towards mid on.
Full again on off, worked to mid on.
Full and on off, Joe Root clips it through mid-wicket. The fielder there runs to his left and cuts it off. He keeps it down to three.
