Fullish on off, Root pushes it towards covers.
On a length, on off. Root guides it to third man for one.
Length ball on off, Malan blocks it out to the off side.
Fuller from Siraj, on middle and leg, Malan plays it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Beautifully placed! Full again on middle, Dawid Malan gets right underneath the ball and whips it through mid-wicket. He fetches himself a boundary.
Short of a length, on leg. Malan looks to pull but misses.
Good-length ball, outside off. Root leaves it alone.
Length ball outside off, Root works it towards deep square leg for one.
On a length, outside off. Malan taps it to point for a run.
On the pads, Root helps it on its way towards the fine leg region for a run.
Good-length ball on off, Malan pushes it towards deep cover for a single. England lead by 200 now.
Length ball on off, Root defends it right under his eyes.
Short of a length, on middle. Malan pulls it towards fine leg for a single.
Short ball on leg, Root leaves it untouched.
Short ball on middle, Root pulls away but miscues. The ball goes off the top edge towards fine leg for a single.
Length ball on the pads, Malan clips it to fine leg for one.
Length ball on off, Root dabs it on the off side for a quick single.
Good-length ball on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
A short ball, on off. Root stays back and pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Short ball on middle, Malan leaves it alone.
A length ball, on off, Malan defends it out.
Sharma serves it on middle. Malan flicks it to mid-wicket and takes off for a single.
Back of a length and on off. Root hangs back and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
A length ball, sliding down the leg side. Malan stays back and looks to flick it away but misses. Rishabh Pant moves to his right and collects the ball.
A length ball, on off. Root stays back and pushes it to cover for a single.
A touch short, on off. Malan stays back and swings his blade. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards third man. They take one.
FOUR! Well played. This is the gap he was looking for. A short ball, on off. Root stays back and pulls it to deep square leg. The ball races away to the boundary.
A touch short, on off. Root pulls it through square leg, but does not middle it this time. The batters take a single.
Full-length ball, down the leg side. Malan looks to flick it away but misses.
Full and on off. Malan pushes it to cover.
Flatter, full and on the pads. Root looks to flick it away but misses and gets hit on the pads. Jadeja puts in an appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Maybe, there was a thin inside edge.
Full and on off. Malan defends it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball, on off. Malan pushes it out.
Tossed up, on off. Malan defends it out watchfully.
Full and on middle, Malan works it on the leg side.
Loopy ball on off, Malan prods and looks to defend but misses. There is a loud appeal for an LBW from Jadeja and Pant but nothing from the umpire.
A length ball, on off. Root defends it to cover.
On a length, around off. Root stays inside the crease and tucks it to mid-wicket.
A length ball, on the pads. Root stays back and flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Siraj serves it on a length and on off. Malan blocks it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Shot of authority. A full-length ball and on the fourth stump line. Malan leans back a bit and creams it through the square on the off side. The ball races away to the fence.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Virat Kohli trusted his bowler and went for the review reluctantly. Siraj serves a length ball, down the leg side. Malan stays back and looks to flick it away but misses. Was there some noise? Few of the Indian players put up an appeal, but the umpire is not interested. Even Pant was not excited. Siraj though convinces the skipper and they take it upstairs. The UltraEdge shows there was some spike as the ball passed the bat. India strike right at the stroke of tea. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 2.
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary: Flatter ball on middle, Root nudges it to mid on.
Flatter and quicker on leg, Root looks to defend but misses. Indian players appeal for an LBW but turned down. Probably going down the leg side.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on leg, worked on the leg side.
Short and on middle, Root rocks back and punches it back to the bowler.
Outside off, Root cuts it but finds backward point.
Short of a length, on leg, Jonny Bairstow glances it towards fine leg for a single.
Good-length ball on middle, Root watchfully blocks it out.
Short of a length, on off. Root taps it towards covers.
Length ball on off, Root pushes it towards covers.
Length ball on off, Root tucks it through mid-wicket for one. 300 up for England.
Good-length ball on off, angling in. Bairstow works it off the shoulder of the bat on the leg side. A single taken.
Full and on leg, Bairstow clears his front leg and jams it out to mid on.
Flatter ball on off, Bairstow defends it out off the front foot.
Full again on off, Bairstow blocks it out.
Loopy ball on off, pushed back to the bowler.

NOT OUT! Flatter ball on off, Jonny Bairstow drives it but it hits the silly point fielder. The ball goes off his shoes and flies towards the keeper. India appeal for a catch but the umpire is not sure. He takes it upstairs. Replay rolls in and shows that the ball had clearly bounced on the deck.
Full and on middle, defended.
Fuller in length, on off. Root drives it to mid off.
Length ball on off, Root taps it towards backward point for a single.
Edge but safe! Good-length ball outside off, Jonny Bairstow puts a stride forward and looks to defend. The ball kisses the outside edge but falls short of the second slip.
Slightly fuller and on middle, Bairstow works it to mid on.
Good-length ball around off, Jonny Bairstow tries to defend it off the front foot as he wants to have a feel of it. The ball zips past the outside edge.
Short of a length, on off. JB is solid in his defense.
Flatter ball on middle, a little bit of turn there. Root watchfully defends it on the off side.
Short and on off, tapped to point.
Full and on middle, Root knocks it back to the bowler.
Full again on the pads, Root clips it towards square leg for a single.
Flatter and quicker on middle, defended out.
On the pads, tucked on the leg side.
FOUR! In the air, but safe! Good-length ball outside off, Joe Root hangs back and cuts it very late. The ball goes past the diving third slip fielder for a boundary.
On a length, on middle, Root nudges it through mid-wicket. He pushes hard for the second run and gets it comfortably.
Length ball on off, Root lunges forward and taps it to point.
Good-length ball, angling in from off, Root defends it off the front foot.
Outside off, Root drives but straight to the mid off fielder.

FOUR! Second boundary of the over! This one was right off the middle of the bat. Length ball on off, Joe Root opens the full face of the bat and drives it towards long off for a boundary. 100 overs up, England are 313/3 with a lead of 235 runs.
Floated it up on off, driven towards extra cover.
FOUR! Jonny Bairstow gets into the act now! Full and on leg, Jonny Bairstow clears his front leg and works it to long on for a boundary.
FOUR! Through the off side now! Flatter ball outside off, Jonny Bairstow puts a big stride forward and creams it through covers for another boundary.
On off, blocked out.
Loopy ball on leg, pushed back to the bowler.
Very full and on middle, attacking the stumps, Bairstow hits it back to the bowler.
Good-length ball on off, Root does well to block that out from the crease.
Length ball outside off, Root guides it to backward point for a single.
Short ball on off, Jonny Bairstow sways away from it.
FOUR! Jonny Bairstow has decided to cash in! Sharma pitches a length ball outside off, Jonny Bairstow cuts it through point for a boundary.
On a length, outside off. Bairstow cuts it towards deep point only for a single this time.
Fuller in length on middle, Root works it towards wide of mid on for a quick single. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. England extend their lead to 250 now.
Flatter ball down the leg side, Joe Root gets low and looks to sweep but misses.
Loopy ball on middle, pushed towards extra cover.
Flatter and quicker on middle, Root inside-edges it towards square leg for a run.
Floated it up on middle, blocked out.
On middle, worked on the leg side.
Loopy ball on middle, pushed back to the bowler. Ravindra Jadeja collects the ball and throws it at the bowler's end. He appeals for a run out but Joe Root was well inside the crease.
Good-length ball on off, Root stays deep in the crease and punches it back to the bowler.

FOUR! CENTURY! Another day, another Test century for Root. 23rd Test century for him. And his second at Headingly. Ishant Sharma overpitches it on middle, Joe Root nudges it through mid-wicket for a boundary. He hops and punches the air with his bat in joy. The crowd is up on its feet and what a moment it is for the homeboy. He receives a big hug from his fellow partner. He is seriously unstoppable.
Short of a lenght, outside off. Root cuts it to deep backward point for one.
Length ball on off, Bairstow blocks it out.
Full and on leg, Bairstow clips it towards deep square leg for a single.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and on off, blocked out.
Full again on middle, defended out watchfully.
Short and outside off, Jonny Bairstow hangs back and cuts it towards point.
Flatter ball on leg, Jonny nudges it to mid-wicket for a single.
Loopy ball on off, driven towards mid off.
An action replay of the previous delivery. This one is driven towards mid off as well.
Play and a miss! Good-length ball outside off, Jonny Bairstow tries to cut it away but misses.
This one is full and on off, Bairstow covers his stumps and blocks it out.
Short of a length on off, pulled to mid-wicket.
Good-length ball on off, Bairstow pushes it back to the bowler.
On a good length, on middle. Bairstow tucks it to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on leg, Bairstow clips it to deep square leg for one.
SIX! What a shot! Flatter ball on middle, Jonny Bairstow gets under it and smokes it over long on for a maximum. The crowd is enjoying that.
On middle, nudged on the leg side for a single.
Loopy ball on off, Root defends it on the off side.
Full and on off, driven towards deep cover for a single.
Floated it up on middle, Bairstow is solid in his defense.
FOUR! Another boundary for Bairstow! This one was flatter, on leg, Jonny Bairstow gets low and sweeps it fine to collect a boundary.
Shami starts with a length ball on off, Root pushes it back to the bowler.
Short ball on off, Root hops and carves it over covers for a run. 350 up for England.

OUT! TAKEN! That is a really good catch from the skipper. Shami bowls a length ball just around off, Jonny Bairstow couldn't resist and has a poke at it. The ball nips away just enough to find the outside edge. It flies towards Virat Kohli at first slip who takes a good low catch moving to his left. Mohammed Shami gets the breakthrough. Jonny Bairstow walks back to the pavilion.
Howout: c Virat Kohli b Mohammed Shami

Commentary: On a good length, on off. Buttler defends it back to the bowler.
Length ball on off, Buttler pushes it towards covers.
Length ball on leg, Buttler flicks it but it hits the chin pad of the short leg fielder.
Flatter ball on leg, Root clips it on the leg side.
On middle, blocked out.
Short and on middle, Root goes back and nudges it to square leg for one.
On off, blocked out on the off side.
On the pads, Buttler defends it on the leg side.
Yet again, on the pads, Jos Buttler nudges it to mid-wicket. He gets off the mark with a single.
Back of a length, on off. Buttler hops and works it towards covers for a quick single.
Fuller in length, on off. Root pushes it back to the bowler.
Beaten! Good-length ball on off, Joe Root looks to cut it away but misses. He gets beaten on the outside edge.
Short of a length, on off. Root goes back and defends.
On a length, on off. Root pushes it towards covers.
Length ball on off, Root blocks it right under his eyes.
Flatter ball on off, Buttler pushes it to covers.
Loopy ball on leg, Jos Buttler uses his feet and looks to work it on the leg side. The ball goes off the leading edge towards covers.
On the pads, tucked on the leg side for a single.
Quicker ball on middle, blocked out.
Tossed up, full and on off, pushed to extra cover.
Flatter ball on leg, Root works it to mid-wicket for a run.
Good-length ball, around off. Root guides it towards deep point for a single.
FOUR! Edgy! On a length outside off, Jos Buttler looks to push it on the off side but miscues. The ball goes off the outside edge past the second slip and gully fielder for a boundary.

OUT! TAKEN! Jos Buttler's drought of runs continues! Shami bowls it on the pads, Jos Buttler flicks it but straight to the fielder at square leg. Ishant Sharma is stationed there and takes the simplest of catches. Jos Buttler is disappointed with himself. Virat Kohli is pumped up. Half the side back in the hut now for England. Mohammed Shami gets his third.
Howout: c Ishant Sharma b Mohammed Shami

Commentary: Good-length ball on off, Ali defends it to mid-wicket.
Good-length ball, outside off. Moeen Ali shoulders arms.
Good-length ball, around off. Moeen Ali has a poke at it but misses. The ball whizzes past the outside edge and carries through to the keeper.
Loopy ball on off, pushed on the off side.
Flatter ball on leg, Root nudges it to square leg.
On off, blocked out.
On the pads, worked to deep square leg for a single.
Floated it up, outside off. Ali leaves it alone.

Tossed up ball on off, Moeen Ali looks to defend but misses. The ball hits the top of the front pad and goes to first slip. Big appeal from the Indian players but nothing from the umpire. There wasn't an inside edge and Ajinkya Rahane anyway drops it at first slip.
Full on off, Root drives it towards covers. Ajinkya Rahane does well to stop that.
On off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
On off, this is guided through point for one.
FOUR! Lovely stroke! On a length and around off, this is driven on the up through covers for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle and leg, tucked to square leg for a single.
Full and on off, Moeen Ali sweeps it towards deep square leg for a single.
Flatter ball on off, driven towards cover.
FOUR! What a shot! Don't think Joe Root can do anything wrong today! Flatter ball on middle, Joe Root reverse-sweeps it towards third man for a boundary.
On middle, blocked out.
Loopy ball on off, Root pushes it towards covers for a run.
On middle, blocked.
Outside off, it is guided through point for one.
Yet again outside off, left alone.
One more delivery outside off, Ali shoulders arms to this one.
Two more! Well fielded! On the pads, this is worked fine. The fielder at fine leg runs to his left and does well to keep it down to two.
Good length and on middle, Ali blocks it out nicely.
FOUR! Cheeky! Just used the pace of the bowler! On middle, Root goes down on one knee and plays the paddle sweep, it goes down to the fine leg fence.
On middle, Root works it to mid-wicket.
Lands it on off, it turns a little. Root looks to defend, it goes off the outer to point.
Another one on middle, kept out.
On off, Root pushes it through covers for one.
Jadeja darts it on off, blocked.
Good length and on off, it is kept out.

OUT! TIMBER! Jasprit gets the better of Root! Just the wicket India wanted. End of an outstanding innings, he walks off to a huge round of applause! He though misses a straight delivery, it probably just stayed a little low. India too were in a little bit of disbelief as to how has he missed it and hence it was a mild celebration. Or maybe they are quite behind the game and hence, it was a mild one. This lands on off and comes in with the angle. Root ends up playing outside the line. It goes between bat and pad and hits the middle pole. The skipper yet again has done his job. Can India now make quick work of the last 4 wickets?
Howout: b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary: Good length and on off, blocked.
Outside off, Curran shoulders arms to this one.
Very full and on middle, Curran plays it back to the bowler.
BEATEN! Loose from Curran! Shorter and outside off, Curran looks to push at it, he does so away from the body. Curran is beaten.
Outside off, Ali initially looks to leave, the ball then turns back in. He then tries to get his bat down to play, it goes off the bottom but well short of first slip.
Full and on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
On the stumps, Ali blocks it out.

OUT! TAKEN! Ravindra Jadeja bags another! Flurry of wickets for India. Jadeja bowls a flatter ball on off, Moeen Ali lifts it straight down the throat of the mid on fielder who is a little deep. Axar Patel, the substitute fielder completes the catch without any trouble. Moeen Ali is livid with himself.
Howout: c sub Axar Patel b Ravindra Jadeja

Commentary: Full and on off, Craig Overton blocks it out.
Flatter-ball on middle and leg, Craig Overton nudges it on the leg side.
Length ball, on off. Sam Curran pushes it back to the bowler.

FOUR! Curran is off the mark! A touch fuller from Bumrah outside off, Sam Curran puts a stride forward and drives it through covers for a boundary. He will be so delighted after that boundary. He had come into this game after two ducks.
On a length, on middle and leg, Curran is solid in his defense.
On off, punched to covers.
Back of a length, on middle. Curran does well to hop and block it out.

A low full toss on off, Curran drives it back towards the bowler, Bumrah gets low, he gets a hand to it, he takes some pace off the delivery, the fielder at mid off gets across and keeps it down to one.
Short and on off, Curran blocks it out from the crease.
Flatter ball on middle, clipped on the leg side.
Quicker ball outside off, left alone.
Full and on off, patted back to the bowler.
FOUR! Well played! Slightly short and outside off, Sam Curran rocks back and cuts it towards deep backward point for a boundary.
On off, worked to mid-wicket.
A low full toss on off, Overton inside-edges it to mid on.
FOUR! Good-length ball, outside off. Craig Overton cuts it late and the ball flies past the third slip and gully fielders for a boundary.
On a length, on off. Overton gets forward and blocks.
Back of a length, on off. Overton looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge. The ball rolls past backward point for a couple of runs.
Slower ball outside off, Overton dabs it to point for one.
On off, Curran defends it back to the bowler. No ball signaled as Bumrah has overstepped.
Length ball on off, pushed back to the bowler again.
Loopy ball on off, defended out.
Slower through the air, on off. Pushed back to the bowler.
Flatter ball on middle, nudged on the leg side.
Full and on off, Overton puts a stride forward and blocks.
On the pads, Overton glances it to short fine leg.
Full and on middle, Overton pushes it to wide of mid on for a brace.
Back of a length, on middle, Curran gets in the line of the ball and defends.
This one is on the pads, Curran nudges it towards square leg for a quick single.
Good-length ball, angling in. Overton pushes it to mid on.
Fuller in length, on off. Overton wrists it to mid on.
Full and on the stumps, Overton clips it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball on middle and leg, Curran watchfully blocks it out.
Loopy ball on off, Overton prods and defends.
Full and on the stumps, Overton defends it on the leg side.
Flatter ball on off, Overton watchfully defends it out.

FOUR! Overton takes the aerial route and gets a reward. Loopy ball on middle, Craig Overton heaves it towards long on for a boundary. This guy can bat, this is what England were missing in the last Test, they had a longer tail but this time they have someone who can genuinely bat after Curran.
On middle, Overton blocks it out off the front foot.
Fuller and flatter on middle, Craig lunges forward and defends it out.
Good-length ball on middle, angling away. Curran taps it towards covers.
Length ball on off, Curran pushes it towards mid off.
In the air, but safe! Length ball on off, Sam Curran lifts it over mid off. Ravindra Jadeja gives it a chase but the ball falls well ahead of him. Two taken.
Back of a length, on off. Curran defends it to point.
Slightly fuller this time, on off. Curran works it on the off side with soft hands. He calls for a quick single but is sent back by Overton.

Tight single! On off, Curran pushes it to mid off for a quick single. Ravindra Jadeja collects the ball quickly and fires a throw at the bowler's end but misses. You don't take a risk when Jadeja is the man. Sam Curran is lucky that didn't hit the stumps. Had that hit, Curran would have been a goner.
Sam Curran advances down the track, Ishant sees him advancing and shortens the length. Curran looks to defend but this goes more off the outer half towards point for one.
Fuller in length, on off. Overton nudges it to mid on.
FOUR! Superb shot! Slightly full from Ishant, on leg. Craig Overton flicks it off his pads through mid-wicket for a boundary.
On a length, outside off. Overton smashes it towards deep point but will only get one.
On the pads, Curran tickles it down to fine leg for a single.
Length ball on off, Overton defends it off the front foot.

OUT! CAUGHT! Short ball on middle, it is well over Curran's head. Sam Curran still goes for the hook shot. He throws the kitchen sink at it but he fails to get on top of the bounce, it goes off the top edge and down the throat of the fielder at deep square leg. Mayank Agarwal, the substitute fielder, is present there and held onto the catch. England lose their eighth wicket. Mohammed Siraj strikes and roars. He is delighted. The hook is probably not the right shot to play, we have seen Rohit get out to that shot a few times and now Curran.
Howout: c sub Mayank Agarwal b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary: Fuller in length, on off. Robinson defends it back to the bowler.
On off, Robinson defends it solidly off the front foot.
Fuller in length again, on off. Robinson watchfully blocks it out.
Good-length ball, on off, angling in. Robinson goes back and blocks it out from the crease.
A slower ball to finish, outside off. Robinson lets it sail through. A wicket maiden from Siraj.
Good-length ball, outside off. Overton leaves it for the keeper to collect.
FOUR! Short and well outside off. A tired ball rather from Ishant Sharma. Craig Overton rocks back and cuts it through cover-point for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone by Overton.
Length ball, on off. Overton knocks it back to the bowler.
Short of a length, outside off. Overton steers it towards deep point for a single.

NOT OUT! Sharma bowls a full ball, on off. Ollie Robinson does well to bring his bat down. He inside-edges it onto the pads. An appeal from Ishant Sharma and Co. for an LBW but the umpire shakes his head. Virat Kohli thinks for a while and then opts for a review. UltraEdge shows a spike as the ball passes the bat. Massive inside edge and Ollie Robinson survives the last ball of the day. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 2.
Back of a length, outside off. Overton looks to punch it away but the ball nips away and goes past the outside edge.
Fuller ball, on off. Overton blocks this one out.
Shami bowls a short ball, down the leg side. Left alone by Overton.
Length ball, on off. Overton drives it too straight and hits the stumps at the other end.
FOUR! Cracking shot! Shorter ball, outside off. Overton cuts it past the deep cover fielder and gets a boundary.
FOUR! And more! Length ball, on middle. Overton whips it past mid-wicket for a boundary. The lead crosses 350 now!
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Fuller ball, on off. Pushed back to the bowler.
Loopy ball, around off. Ollie Robinson blocks it out.
Flatter ball, lands outside leg. Ollie Robinson misses the sweep and gets hit on the pads.
Flatter ball, around leg. Ollie Robinson looks to swipe it away but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Fuller ball, on off. Pushed to covers.
Length ball, outside off. Overton looks to block but is beaten.
On a length, outside off. Craig Overton blocks it from the crease.
Fuller ball, on off. Craig Overton gets on the front foot to block it out.
Length ball, on leg. Overton gets hit on the pads while looking to flick.

OUT! LBW! Shami strikes early for India! Full ball, on off. Overton looks to work it to the leg side but gets hit on the pads. The umpire raises the finger right away. The review is taken by Overton. But UltraEdge has a flat line and Ball Tracker shows three reds.
Howout: lbw b Mohammed Shami

Commentary: Full ball, down the leg side. Anderson misses the flick.
Full ball, on leg. Worked to the leg side.
Length ball, around off. Ollie Robinson gets the outside edge while looking to block. The man at second slip dives to his right and stops the ball. No ball called.
OUT! BOWLED! There comes the last wicket. Full ball, on off. Ollie Robinson goes for the mighty heave but misses. The ball hits the stumps and England are bowled out for 432!
Howout: b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary: A nice outswinger, it lands outside off. Sharma prods forward and leaves it.
Back of a length, around off. Sharma blocks it from the crease.
Well bowled! Length ball, just outside off. Sharma looks to defend but pulls his bat out at the last moment.
Fuller ball, on off. Sharma prods forward and taps it to the off side.
Full ball, way outside off. Sharma has no interest in offering a stroke.

Length ball, outside off. Sharma gets the outside edge while looking to defend. The ball goes past gully. Haseeb Hameed chases it and dives to pull it back in. Jonny Bairstow throws the ball back in and two runs are taken. India are underway.
Full ball, outside off. Rahul leaves this one alone.
KL Rahul is off the mark! Length ball, on off. He strides forward and pushes it past cover for one.
Back of a length, outside off. Left alone.
On a length, outside off. Sharma covers the stumps and then leaves it.
Length ball, on middle. Sharma gets the inside edge to the leg side for a single.
Back of a length, wide enough for Rahul to leave it with ease.
Outswinger, this starts outside off and nips away. Sharma leaves it alone.
Beaten! This lands on off so Rohit Sharma is forced to play at it. The ball moves away sharply and goes past the outside edge.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Fuller ball, on off. Sharma gets the edge but it falls short of the slip cordon.
Just short again! Length ball, on off. Sharma looks to block but gets the edge again. The ball lands short of the slips yet again.
Length ball, outside off. Sharma leaves this one with ease.
Length ball, on leg. Rahul works it to fine leg for one.
Back of a length, just outside off. Sharma leaves this one.
Back of a length, on off. Blocked out.
On a length, outside off. Sharma leaves this one.
Back of a length, just outside off. Sharma leaves it.
A touch fuller, but wide enough for Sharma to leave it without any fuss.
Here comes the inswinger! Length ball, lands on off and nips back in. Rahul looks to work it away but gets hit high on the pads.
Full ball, on leg. Rahul works it past square leg for one.
Length ball, just outside off. Sharma trusts the bounce and leaves this one.
Back of a length, but quite wide outside off. Left alone yet again by Sharma.
Full ball, on off. Blocked out.
Full ball, on off. Sharma pushes it back to the bowler.
Outside off on a length, KL Rahul shoulders arms.
An action replay of the previous delivery.

Length delivery, around off, KL Rahul prods ahead and looks to block but misses and gets hit on the pad. An appeal but turned down. The height seemed to be an issue. Replays show that the impact was outside off too.
On the pads, clipped through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Fuller, outside off, left alone.
On off, KL gets ahead to defend but misses and gets hit on the pad.
FOUR! Sweetly timed by Rohit Sharma. On a length, outside off, swings away and Rohit Sharma leans ahead and creams this through covers for a boundary.
Short of a length, around off, RS goes back and nudges this to the leg side for a run.
Around off, defended out.
Outside off, KL holds himself back and makes a leave.
Good length on off, Rahul blocks this solidly.
Closer to the off pole on a length, KL comes ahead, sniffs at the ball, and makes a late decision to let the ball be.
Angled into the pads, Sharma nurdles this to deep square leg and rotates the strike.
Short of a length, angling in, Rahul looks to work this to the leg side but misses and gets hit high on the pad.
Similar line and length as the previous ball, Rahul, this time, gets bat on ball as he taps this to the leg side.
Anderson slants a length ball on the body, this is nudged out to the mid on region. 'NO RUN, NO RUN!' quips Rahul.
Length, lands outside off, nips back sharply and hits him Rahul on the thigh pad.
Outside off, short of a length, Rahul keeps a close eye on this and shoulders arms this time.
Around off, Rohit taps this to point.
Left alone as this was bowled outside off.
In the fourth-stump channel, outside off, the ball seams away as Rohit prods forward and makes a leave.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Fourth stump line again, on a length, Sharma leaves it untouched.
Length on off, defended to square leg.
Hurls a good length ball around off, KL Rahul presses forward and blocks it out solidly.
A single as this was nudged in between mid-wicket and square leg.
One more run as Rohit Sharma exploits the same area that KL did on the previous ball. India behind by 338 runs.

NOT OUT! The review works out for India and Rahul as the on-field decision has been overturned. Robinson hurls across a length delivery, around the off pole, the ball hits the deck and nips back in sharply on this occasion. Rahul looks to defend this one but the ball misses his willow and goes onto ping his pad. An appeal and the finger goes up this time. Rahul has a word with Rohit and with just one single second left on the timer, Rahul opts for the same. Ball Tracker shows that the ball was missing the stumps. Good decision by KL Rahul!
On off, defended.
Length outside off, Rahul looks to defend but the ball whistles past the edge to the keeper.
Full ball, on leg. Sharma works it past square leg for one.
Full ball, way outside off. Left alone.
Outswinger but starts way outside off. Rahul leaves this one.
Back of a length, a lot closer to the off pole. But wide enough for Rahul to leave it without any fuss.
Length ball, just outside off. Rahul gets forward but keeps it bat behind the pads to leave it alone.
Fuller ball, lands on the fifth stump. Left alone by Rahul.
Full ball, on off. Sharma whips it to deep square leg for one.

Full ball, on leg. Rahul looks to block it but gets hit on the pads. The ball lobs up and is taken by Haseeb Hameed at short leg. The fielders put in a big appeal for a catch but it is turned down. They do not take the review too.
Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out.
Length ball, but wide enough for Rahul to let the keeper collect it.
Full ball, just outside off. Rahul blocks it out.
On a length, wide outside off. Rahul has no intentions of offering a stroke to this one.
Beaten! Length ball, just outside off. Sharma hangs his bat out but the ball goes past the edge.
And again! Length ball, on off. Sharma looks to block and the ball goes past the edge. Jos Buttler collects it over his head.
Fuller ball, on leg. Worked to the leg side.

Beaten again! Length ball, on off. Sharma looks to block it from the crease but the ball goes past the edge. There is a noise as the ball goes past the bat and an appeal is put in for caught behind. It is turned down and Craig Overton says that it hit the pads. The replay confirms the same.
Length ball, on off. Worked to the leg side.
Full ball, wide enough to be left alone.
Length ball, on leg. Rahul works it to square leg.
Full ball, on off. Rahul looks to block but gets no bat on it.

This comes back in! Full ball, lands on off and comes back in. Rahul looks to work it away but gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW but turned down. Root suggests that there was some bat on it and the replay confirms the same.
Full again, just outside off. Rahul gets the edge while looking to block. The ball goes towards gully.
On a length, wide enough to be left alone.
Beaten again! On a length, lands outside off and comes back in. Rahul looks to block but the ball zips past the outside edge.
Back of a length, around off. Sharma blocks it out. He wants the single but is sent back by Rahul.
Full ball, on leg. Blocked out by Sharma.
Short of third slip! Length ball, on off. Sharma looks to block but gets the edge. But since he is playing with soft hands, the ball lands short of the diving third slip fielder.
Fuller ball, outside off. Left alone now.
Length ball, on leg. Sharma works it past mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
On a length, just outside off. Sharma decides to leave it at the last moment. The ball hits the bat and goes towards the slip cordon.
On a length, angling in around off, Rahul strides forward and middles his push towards point for one.
Way outside off, left alone.

Slightly behind the good length, lands outside off and comes back in nicely. Rohit Sharma looks to work this to the leg side, but misses to get hit on the pad. No ball called as Ollie Robinson has overstepped.

SIX! That's the Rohit Sharma that we all know. It is a loose delivery and Sharma does not miss out. Short ball, outside off this time, Rohit Sharma just waits and then pumps this one all the way over third man for a biggie.
On middle, nudged to the leg side.
Sharma has just watchfully blocked this out.
Around off, kept out.
Slower ball, on middle and leg, flicked to the short mid-wicket fielder.
That is defended solidly off the front foot by Rahul.
Length outside off, left alone.
On a good length, around off, KL looks to defend, but gets an inside edge to the leg side for a run.
There is the short ball from Overton to Rohit. It is on the body and Rohit pulls this to deep square leg for one.
Fourth-stump channel, length ball, KL shoulders arms.
Fullish ball on off, RS pushes this to the mid on fielder, where James Anderson dives to his left and stops the ball well.
Down the leg side, RS misses his flick.
Rohit Sharma has just watchfully blocked this out.
Rohit defends this length ball out to the off side.

FOUR! Nicely clipped away. Sharma waited for the ball to swing into him and then he decided to whip this one away. Length delivery, lands it on middle and the ball nips in, Rohit Sharma just tucks this wonderfully through mid-wicket.
On off, blocked.
Full, really full around off, KL digs this one out.
Good length on off, Rahul pushes it back to Overton.
Around off, nudged to the mid-wicket region.
Outside the off pole, good length, Rahul defends inside the line and misses the ball.
A touch fuller, around off, Rahul blocks.

OUT! EDGED AND CAUGHT! What a catch this is by Bairstow. Wonderful delivery too from Overton and just at the stroke of Lunch, KL Rahul's innings has been cut short. Outstanding piece of cricket from England and they will head back as the happier side. Overton serves this on a length, around the off pole, KL Rahul is forced to play at this due to the angle, but the ball nips away enough to catch the outside edge. The ball goes in between Joe Root (first slip) and Jonny Bairstow (second slip) and Bairstow dives to his left and takes a one-handed stunner. Jubilation for England here. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 3!
Howout: c Jonny Bairstow b Craig Overton

Commentary: Leg bye. A length ball, on the pads, Rohit Sharma looks to tuck it to the leg side but misses and the ball takes the pad and goes to the leg side. A leg bye is taken as Anderson appeals. The umpire says nothing though.
Outside off, on a length, Cheteshwar Pujara looks to block inside the line and misses.
Strayed on the pads, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks this to the right of Dawid Malan at leg slip, who dives that side and stops the ball.
This is pitched up, outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara just shoulders arms.
There's the nip-backer! On a length, on middle and swings down the leg side, CP looks to flick but misses and Jos Buttler dives to his left and stops the ball.
Around off, length, Pujara defends it out.
Length ball, on leg. Sharma gets hit on the pads while looking to flick it.
Fuller ball, outside off. Blocked out.

Length ball, on off. Sharma looks to block it but gets hit on the pads. An appeal is put in but the umpire turns it down. Root suggests that this might be going over the stumps so does not review it. Replay confirms the same.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Very full, outside off. Sharma blocks it out.
Fuller ball, on off. Sharma blocks it off the front foot.
Length ball, on off. Pujara gets the outside edge while looking to block but the ball falls short of the slip cordon.
On a length, around off. Blocked out.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Full ball, on leg. Pujara whips it past mid-wicket for a boundary.
On a length, but wide enough for Pujara to leave it.
Length ball, just outside off. Pujara hangs his bat out to defend but gets beaten.
Full ball, on leg. Flicked away for a couple by Pujara.
On a length, just outside off. Sharma is beaten as he looks to defend this one.
Full ball, on off. Nicely driven by Sharma but Overton gets low and stops the ball.
Length ball, around off. Pushed to gully.
On a length, on off. Sharma blocks it out from the crease.
Length ball, on leg. Sharma works it to square leg for a single now.
FOUR! Punished. Full and straight. Pujara whips it past mid-wicket for a boundary.
Outswinger, just outside off. Sharma thinks about playing it but leaves it at the last moment.
Jaffa! On a length, on off. Sharma looks to block it from the crease but the ball nips away just enough to go past the outside edge.
On a length, around off. Sharma gets the outside edge past gully. Overton chases the ball and dives to stop it just before the ropes. Three taken.
FOUR! Punished yet again! Full and on the pads. Pujara whips it past square leg for yet another boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Pujara trusts the bounce and lets this go.
Length ball, on off. Pujara pushes it to fourth slip.
Lovely shot for nothing. Full ball, on off. Sharma drives it straight but Overton gets low yet again to stop it.
Length ball, way down the leg side. Sharma misses the flick.
Back of a length, on leg. Sharma taps it to the leg side.
Back of a length, around off. Sharma blocks it from the crease.
Full ball, on off. Sharma pushes it to point.
Good-length ball, on middle. Sharma is solid in his defence of this one.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Lands on a length, on off and comes back in. Pujara is hit high on the pads while looking to block.
Full ball, just outside off. Left alone.
On a length, outside off. Pujara makes a leave.
Fuller ball, around off. Cheteshwar Pujara comes on the front foot to block it.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Back of a length, outside off. Blocked out.
Length ball, around off. Sharma is beaten as he looks to defend.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Full but wide enough for Sharma to leave it.
Length ball, on off. Sharma defends it towards point.
On a length again, on off. Sharma works it to mid on.
Full ball, wide outside off. Left alone.
Full and way outside off. Buttler dives to his right but cannot stop. The batters cross over.
Length ball, on off. Sharma gets the inside edge to the leg side while looking to defend.
Over the fielder! Length ball, on off. Sharma chips it just over mid off. Ali chases it and keeps it down to two.
FOUR! Top shot! Full ball, way outside off. Sharma leans into it and drives it past point for a boundary.
Length ball, wide enough to be left alone with ease.
Fuller inswinger, on middle. Sharma pushes it to mid on.
Length ball, on off. Pujara blocks it out.
Length ball, around off. Pujara taps it to the off side.
Full ball, outside off. Pujara leaves it well.
FOUR! Nicely played. Short of a length, outside off. Pujara works it past the slip cordon. Haseeb Hameed chases it and dives but cannot keep the ball in play.
Length ball, on leg. Cheteshwar Pujara gets hit on the pads while looking to block.
FOUR! More runs for Pujara! Full ball, outside off. Pujara drives it past covers. The fielders chases it and dives but cannot stop the ball.
Length ball, on leg. Sharma looks to flick but gets hit high on the pads.
An action replay of the previous delivery.
Length ball, around off. Blocked out by Sharma.

Rohit Sharma survives an LBW call. Length ball, on off. Sharma looks to block and gets hit on the pads. The appeal for LBW is turned down. England review this but lose the review as Ball Tracker shows that the ball is going over the stumps.
FOUR! Full and way outside off. Sharma carves it over point for a boundary.
Back of a length, around off. Rohit Sharma blocks it out.
Length ball, wide outside off. Left alone.
On a length, just outside off. Left alone.
Length ball, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it out.
Full ball, outside off. Pujara shoulders arms to it.
Fuller again, outside off again. Left alone again.
On a length, outside off. Pujara covers his stumps and leaves it.
A nice full one, tempting Sharma to drive it. Sharma leaves it though.
Length ball, on off. Pushed to mid off.
Length ball, lands outside off and nips back in. Sharma leaves it alone.
Full ball, outside off. Sharma covers his stumps and leaves it alone.
Appeal for LBW. Length ball, on off. Sharma looks to block it but gets hit on the pads. There is a huge appeal for LBW. England want to review this one but they run out of time while trying to do so.
Length ball, outside off. Sharma has no qualms in leaving this one.
Anderson bowls a full one, outside off. Pujara leaves this one for Jos Buttler to collect.
Length ball, outside off. Pujara makes another leave.
On a length, around off. Cheteshwar Pujara stays in his crease and taps it to covers.
FOUR! Pujara has made plenty of runs today when he has been served such balls. Full ball, down the leg side. He flicks it to the fine leg fence.
Length ball, just outside off. Pujara makes a leave to this one.
Peach of a delivery! Anderson lands this outside off and gets it to nip back in. Pujara looks to block it but gets no bat on it.
Ollie Robinson slips this one down the leg side. Sharma looks to flick it away but the ball is way outside his reach.
This is a better line. This lands on off and nips back in. Sharma looks to flick it but gets hit on the pads. The players do not put in a big appeal as the ball was probably going down the leg side.
A touch shorter by Ollie Robinson. Back of a length, on off. Rohit Sharma is solid in his defence of this one.
A touch fuller now, on off. Sharma gets on the front foot to block it out.
Full again, on off. Sharma pushes it back to the bowler. No ball called as Ollie Robinson has overstepped.
Short of a length now, around middle. Sharma works it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller ball, around off. Pujara gets forward and pushes it to the off side.
Anderson bowls a length ball, in the line of the stumps. Sharma had looked very solid in his defence so far and does the same here.
On a length, right on the off pole. Sharma pushes it to mid off now.
Anderson bowls the inswinger now. This lands on off and comes back in. Rohit Sharma though is quite solid in his defence yet again.
A hint of away swing on that one! Full again, around off. Sharma plays it back to Anderson.
Anderson persists with the full length, this is on off. Sharma pushes it back to the bowler again.
Length ball, on the fifth-stump line. Rohit Sharma gets a nice stride in and defends the ball right under his eyes.
This lands on a length, just outside off and nips back in. Pujara covers his stumps and then leaves it alone.
Length again, making Pujara play at this one. He blocks it back on the deck.
Well left. Short of a length, just outside off. Pujara trusts the bounce of this and leaves it. The ball goes over the off pole.
Ollie Robinson slips one on the pads now. Pujara looks to work it to the leg side but gets hit on the pads. No appeal is put in as it was likely sliding down the leg stump.
A touch fuller, on middle. Pujara gets a stride forward and blocks it to the leg side.
Ollie Robinson goes wider with the length ball now. Cheteshwar Pujara has no intention of playing that one.
Anderson bowls a touch shorter one now, on the fifth stump. Rohit Sharma plays it with soft hands back on the deck.
Full ball, on off. Sharma pushes it back to Anderson.
Play and a miss! Length ball, outside off. Sharma has his feet glued to the crease as he looks to punch it. The ball nips away and goes past the outside edge.
Fuller inswinger now, around off. Sharma gets it from the inner half towards mid on for a single.
On a length, right on the off pole. Cheteshwar Pujara stays in his crease and blocks it with soft hands.
Full ball, on the pads. Flicked to mid-wicket.
Full ball, on leg. Sharma blocks it out.
FOUR! Oh that is a glorious stroke! Curran bowls a full one, on off. Sharma offers the full face of the bat and drives it straight down the ground for a boundary.
FOUR! Tell you what, when he bats like this, it is a treat to watch! Curran pitches it up yet again, a touch wider outside off. Sharma leans into it and drives it through covers for a boundary.

There comes his 50. This is a much-needed 50 for India. Length ball, lands on off and nips back in. Sharma works it to fine leg for a run. This hasn't been a typical Rohit Sharma innings but he has played according to the situation and India would hope that he carries on to get a big one.
Full ball, on off. Pujara hits it down the ground but does not middle it. The man from mid on gets across and stops it.
On a length, around off. Pujara gets forward and blocks it.
A length ball, on off by James Anderson and a solid front-foot defence by Rohit Sharma.
Back of a length, outside off. Sharma stays back and pushes it to covers.
Fuller ball, on off. Sharma pushes it towards cover.
A length ball, right on the off pole. Sharma gets behind the line of the ball and taps it towards point.
Fuller ball, outside off. A hint of away movement on that one but Rohit Sharma is very solid in his defence.
Full ball, on off. Sharma offers the full face of the bat and plays it to mid on.
Length on middle, defended to the leg side.
Fuller in length this time, on middle, clipped through mid-wicket for an easy couple.
Around off, on a length, CP defends it out.
Curran now digs a short ball, on middle and leg, Cheteshwar Pujara just ducks under this one.

FOUR! Another boundary for Pujara. He has been scoring runs at a brisk pace so far. Good reaction from him too. Good length, around off and middle, Cheteshwar Pujara goes back and whips this one nicely through square leg.
On off, pushed to mid off for a quick single.
Floated on off, CP skips down and pads this one away to the off side.
Flatter, on off, punched to the mid on region.
Flatter again, around off and middle, Pujara goes back and works this through mid-wicket for a run.
Tossed up, around off, Rohit skips down and defends.
On middle, nudged to the square leg fielder.
A tad short, around off, Sharma knocks this through mid-wicket and takes one.
Down the leg side, Rohit misses his flick.
Fullish, on the pads, whipped to fine leg for one.
A touch behind the good-length area, around the hips, Cheteshwar Pujara misses his flick and gets hit high on the pad.
Full, on the pads this time, Pujara dabs this to the on side.
Pujara's flick finds the fieder at square leg.
A couple now! 100 up for India too! Back of a length, slanting away outside off, Pujara just guides this one through short third man and they return for the second.
Tossed up, outside off, Rohit is in two minds. Should I hang back, should I go front? Stays back, in the end, and defends it out.
Full on off, pushed to covers.
Again, Moeen goes fuller, just around off, Rohit pushes it to the off side.
Darted on the pads, Rohit looks to flick, but the ball misses his blade and gets hit on the pads.
Sharma steps out to the pitch of the ball this time and guides it past point. Rotates the strike.
Around off, punched back to Ali to end the over. India behind by 252 now!
Angles a length ball around off, Rohit defends this to covers.
Similar line and length as the previous ball, this time, Sharma taps this to the short mid-wicket fielder.
Slants this slightly too much and slips it down the leg side, Sharma misses his tuck and Buttler does well to move to his left and collect.
Length around off, kept out.
On a length, angled across off, Sharma thinks of playing this to the leg side but closes the face of his bat early. The ball takes the leading edge and goes safely to point.
Pushed away nicely to the mid off fielder. Maiden for Sam Curran!
Starts with a short ball, outside off, Pujara awkwardly punches this to point. He sends Rohit back quickly, as there was no run there.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.
Fuller, on off, Cheteshwar Pujara skips down and pads this one away.

Two is the call and two is what they get! A touch shortish again, outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara camps back and pumps this wide of the cover fielder. The man in the deep runs to his left and stops the ball. Two taken.
Outside off, slapped to deep point by CP for a single.
Another single again as Rohit Sharma punches this to the deep cover fielder.
FOUR! That shot had some control from Sharma. This is bowled shortish, on the body, does not rise too much and Rohit Sharma finds it easy to swivel and hook this to the deep square leg fence.
On the body, Rohit drops this to the leg side and hands the strike to Pujara.
Fullish, outside off, Pujara comes forward and smothers the ball out.
Curran comes 'round the wicket and bowls a length ball on the pads, easily clipped to the right of fine leg for a run.
Around off, length, Rohit defends this to the leg side.
Well negotiated by Sharma! On a length, around off and middle, Rohit blocks it nicely. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 3!
Short ball, way outside off. Pujara rocks back and chops it straight towards short cover.
FOUR! Perfect execution of that shot! Back of a length, outside off. Pujara rides the bounce and guides it past point for a boundary.
Fuller ball, on off. Pujara defends it off the front foot.
Short of a length, outside off. Pushed to covers now.
Fuller ball, on off. Pujara looks to block it to the off side but gets it from the inner half back to the bowler.
On a length, around off. Pujara punches it to mid on.
Back of a length, outside off. Sharma stands tall and pushes it to cover. They think of taking one for a second but decide against it.
Back of a length, outside off. Sharma stays in his crease and blocks it out.
Outswinger, but starts way outside off. Sharma gets on the front foot and then leaves it alone.

OUT! LBW! Umpire's call sends Rohit Sharma back! He is very disappointed. Ollie Robinson strikes just after Tea and this is exactly what England wanted. It has come against the run of play as well, as Rohit was looking very settled out in the middle. Ollie Robinson fires a full ball, angling in, on middle. Sharma looks to whip it away but the ball comes back in just a touch and hits him on the pads. England put in a big appeal and the umpire raises the finger. Sharma reviews this. There is no bat on that one but Ball Tracker has umpire's call on wickets hitting the outer half of the leg pole! This is just what England needed to start this session. A really, really good knock by Sharma ends. He would have wanted to carry on to score a big one. He whacks the ground in anger and walks back to the hut.
Howout: lbw b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Full ball, right on the off pole. Kohli gets forward and blocks it.
Back of a length, but wide enough for the Indian skipper to leave it.
Full ball, around off. Pujara looks to block it to the off side but gets it from the inner half back on the deck.
Back of a length, outside off. Pujara pushes it to covers.
Full ball, down the leg side. Pujara misses the flick.
Back of a length now, around off. Pujara taps it to the off side.
Fuller ball, on leg. Pujara taps it to the leg side.
Full again, but straighter this time. Pujara works it towards fine leg for a single. He will keep the strike.
Length ball, outside off. Pujara makes a leave.
Back of a length, outside off. Pujara taps it towards point looking for one but Kohli sends him back.
Full ball, on the fifth stump. Pujara covers the stumps and then lets Buttler collect it.
On a length, just outside off. Pujara leaves it alone.
Full ball, but on the pads. Pujara works it to fine leg for a single.
Robinson bowls it on a length and tempts Kohli to play at it. But the Indian skipper leaves it.
Short ball, on off. Pujara ducks under this one with ease.

FOUR! 50 for Cheteshwar Pujara! This has been an innings where he has scored runs at a brisk pace. Shorter ball, outside off. Pujara pulls it to the mid-wicket fence. He soaks in all the applause from his mates in the hut!
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Length ball, way down the leg side. So down the leg side that even Jos Buttler cannot stop it despite diving to his left. The batters take a bye.
On a length, just outside off. Kohli leaves it.
Length ball, on off. Kohli plays it with soft hands. So, despite getting the edge, the ball drops short of the slip cordon.
Fullish delivery, around off and middle, hits the deck and seams inwards sharply, Pujara looks to flick this one away but the ball takes the pad and goes to the leg side. The batters run the leg bye.
Fuller outside off, VK takes a stride forward but leaves it.
Outside off again, another leave by Virat.

An appeal for LBW but turned down! Back of a length, outside off, angling in, Virat Kohli shoulders arms and the ball jags back in. It kisses his thigh pad and goes to Buttler. An appeal, but the umpire just shakes his head. The camera pans to Root, who decides not to take the review as height could have been an issue. Replays show that the ball was going over the wickets.
Outside off, no shot offered.

NO BALL! Ollie Robinson oversteps this time. On a length, around off, Virat Kohli looks to flick but closes the face of his bat early. The outside edge is induced and the ball goes to covers for one. Kohli is off the mark!
Around off, defended out.
Length around off, Kohli strides forward and blocks it out.
FOUR! Beautifully timed. Kohli gets his first boundary and it is off his nemesis. On a length, on middle and leg, Virat Kohli whips this one through square leg.
Way outside off, VK goes back to shouldering arms.
Darted on the pads, Kohli flicks it to fine leg and rotates the strike.

Short of a length, in the fourth stump channel, Cheteshwar Pujara dabs this one past the slip cordon. Haseeb Hameed chases after this and pulls the ball back, before it touches the ropes. Three taken this time.

FOUR! Lovely. That's the vintage Kohli that we all know. In the fourth-stump channel, on a drivable length, Virat Kohli shows the full face of the bat and creams this through covers. Moves to 10 from 15 balls.

FOUR! Cleverly played. Pujara was taken by surprise, but he did well to adjust. Short ball, around off, it zips through and comes towards him as he sways away. Pujara keeps an angled bat and just lofts this one over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Around off, kept out.
Outside off, no shot offered.
Sharp inswing! Lands around off and nips back in, to ping Pujara on the thigh pad, as he missed his tuck.
Good-length delivery, on off, Pujara comes ahead and blocks.
Around middle, nudged to fine leg for one.
Back of a length, outside off, Pujara moves back and lets the ball through to the keeper.
An action replay of the previous ball.
Three similar sort of deliveries from Anderson and Pujara leaves all of them alone.
Again, outside off, length, Pujara wants nothing to do with it.

FOUR! Looks like James Anderson got frustrated watching Pujara leave everything and hence, serves an inswinger around middle and leg, easy pickings for Cheteshwar Pujara as he clips this to the square leg fence.
FOUR! Again, too straight from Anderson and Pujara is too skilled to leave this unpunished. Fuller, on middle and leg, Pujara whips this to the fine leg fence. India behind by 203 runs now!
Outswinger but this starts way outside off. Kohli covers his stumps and lets this one go.
Much closer to the off pole and much fuller. Kohli blocks it off the front foot.
On a length, this lands outside off and shapes further way. Kohli leaves this one alone now.
Fuller ball, right on the off pole. Kohli blocks it back to the bowler. No ball called as Ollie Robinson oversteps.
Back of a length, on the fifth stump. Kohli leaves this without any fuss.
This starts outside off and comes back in. Kohli works it to mid on.
Full ball, on off. Kohli looks to drive but gets it from the inner half to the mid on fielder.
Full ball, wide outside off. Pujara covers his stumps and then leaves it.
Back of a length, outside off. Pujara leaves it yet again.
FOUR! Lovely shot. Full ball, on off. Pujara drives it down the ground. The man from mid off gets to his right and dives but cannot get there. The ball runs to the fence and Pujara moves to 70.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Length ball, lands outside off and nips away further. Pujara leaves this one.
Full ball, on off. Pujara looks to block but gets the inside edge back on the pads.
Full ball, on off. Kohli nails the cover drive. The man at cover though dives and gets a hand to it. A single is taken.
On a length, angling away from the off pole. Left alone.
Fuller ball, around off. Pujara pushes it to cover.
Back of a length, on leg. Pujara stays in his crease and blocks it to the leg side.
Curran serves a length ball, right in the line of the stumps. Pujara pushes it back to the bowler.
Fuller ball, angling across the off pole. Pujara gets forward and then leaves it.
Back of a length, around off. Kohli blocks it.
Fuller ball, on off. Kohli stays in his crease and defends it.
Good-length ball, around off. Kohli gets behind the line of the ball and then blocks it.
A touch fuller, but wide enough for Kohli to leave it.
Fuller ball, just outside off. Kohli makes a very good leave.
Length ball, around off. Blocked out.
Curran bowls a full ball, on off. Pujara hits it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, on leg. Pujara rides the bounce and taps it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Full ball, on off. Kohli stays solid in his defence.
FOUR! Hammered. Short ball, on leg. With Curran's pace, it is asking to be hit. Kohli rocks back and pulls it hard to the mid-wicket fence.
Fuller ball, angling away from the off pole. Left alone.
Length ball, on off. The ball bounces a touch more and gets the outside edge as Kohli looks to defend. The ball goes to the slip cordon on the bounce.
Back of a length, on off. Pujara taps it to the off side and looks for a quick single but Kohli sends him back.
Back of a length, on off, tapped to point.
Fuller, on the pads, Pujara's clip finds the square leg fielder.
Short of a length, angling inwards around off, Pujara fails to get bat on ball and gets hit high on the pad.
A touch fuller, around off, Cheteshwar Pujara looks to flick but gets the leading edge to the point fielder.
A single as this is clipped to the fine leg fielder.
Length on off, Pujara keeps it out.
Good-length delivery on the pads, nicely flicked to deep square leg for a run.

FOUR! Kohli's fourth boundary brings about the 50-run stand between Kohli and Pujara. The Indian skipper is showing a lot of confidence here. On a length, around middle and leg, good uses of the wrists by Virat as he sends this one through mid-wicket.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller, outside off, Kohli shoulders arms.
On middle and leg, dropped to the leg side.
A touch short, this is pulled awkwardly to the man at mid-wicket.
Fuller, outside off, driven crisply, but straight to the mid off fielder.
In the channel of uncertainty outside off, Pujara leaves it be.
A carbon copy of the previous delivery.
On middle, dropped towards mid-wicket for a quick run.
Kohli gets a couple of runs now. A half-volley near the pads now, VK whips this to deep mid-wicket and comes back for the second run.
Length around off, Pujara blocks well.
Fullish ball, fourth stump channel, Cheteshwar Pujara takes a big stride forward but watches the ball sail past him.
An action replay of the previous ball.
Good-length ball, on off, CP pushes this one back to Jimmy.
Slightly outside the off pole, Pujara just taps this to the off side.
Maiden for Jimmy! Around off, worked to the leg side.
Gives it a lot of air, fuller outside off, this is jammed out to the mid off fielder.
A single as this fuller ball is dug out through the cover region.
Floated outside off, CP dances down and looks to defend, as the ball spins in and pings him on his pad.
Pujara puts on his skates again and his clip finds the mid-wicket fielder.
Around off, pushed to the point region.
A touch short, outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara rocks back and looks to slash it away but misses.
Length ball, on off. Blocked.
On a length, on off. Kohli taps it to the off side and looks for a quick single but is sent back.
On a length, outside off. Pushed to covers.
Fuller ball, around off. Kohli stays in his crease and blocks it out.
A touch shorter and wider outside off. Kohli covers the stumps and then leaves it.
FOUR! Top shot by Kohli! Anderson bowls it full and outside off. Kohli leans into it and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Shorter ball, outside off. Pujara slaps it to deep cover for one.

Tossed up, outside off, Kohli came down the track and looked to flick. But the ball pitched, spun in a little, took the inside edge, hit the pad and lobbed. But well wide of short leg, to his left, towards mid-wicket. Kohli wanted a single but was sent back.
Shorter ball, around off. Blocked out.

NOT OUT! Tossed up, outside off. Kohli looks to block but the ball goes past the edge. Buttler whips the bails off and the TV umpire is called in. They first check for caught behind, but there is no bat on that one. Then, comes the check for stumping. Replays show that Kohli has his back foot just behind the line, so not out is the decision.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Flatter ball, on leg. Kohli works it past square leg for one.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Back of a length, around off. Kohli pushes it to covers.
Anderson bowls it full now, on off. Kohli is solid in his defence.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Fuller ball, around off. Kohli works it to the leg side.
Length ball, on leg. Kohli flicks it away for one.
Shorter ball, on off. Kohli goes back and clips it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Cheteshwar Pujara comes down the track and clips it to deep square leg for one.
Shorter ball, on off. Kohli works it to deep square leg for one.
Shorter ball, outside off. Slapped to deep cover for one.
Tossed up, on off. Virat Kohli blocks it off the front foot.
Shorter ball, on off. Kohli pulls it to deep mid-wicket. Runs are flowing easily for these two here.
Loopy ball, outside off. Left alone.
Fuller ball, on off. Pushed to covers.
Loopy ball, on off. Kohli eases it to long on for one.
Tossed up, outside off. Pujara comes down the track and whips it straight towards mid-wicket.
Darted on the pads. Pujara works it straight to square leg.
Cheteshwar Pujara comes down the track and blocks this one out.
Flatter ball, outside off. Kohli goes back and blocks it out.
Tossed up, outside off. Kohli prods forward and blocks it.
Flatter ball, on off. Pushed to mid-wicket.
Full ball, on off. Pushed to mid on.
Tossed up, on off. Kohli blocks it out.
Shorter ball, around off. Kohli pushes it to mid on.
Flatter ball, around off. Pujara stays in his crease and blocks it.
Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out.
Flatter ball, outside off. Pushed away to the off side.
Shorter ball, on leg. Pujara works it to square leg.
Darted on the pads. Tucked to the leg side by Pujara.
Flatter ball, on off. Pujara blocks it out.
Virat Kohli comes down the track and blocks it out.
Tossed up, on off. Virat Kohli blocks it again.
Shorter ball, on off. Kohli works it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Loopy ball, on leg. Worked to the leg side.

FOUR! Poor ball and punished by Cheteshwar Pujara! Shorter ball, wide outside off. Pujara frees his arms and cuts it past backward point. The fielder chases it but the ball wins the race. He moves to 81 now.
Tossed up, outside off. Pujara gets his front foot to the pitch of the ball and leaves it.
Full ball, on leg. Whipped towards deep square leg. Kohli runs the first one hard, but there is no second one there.
Shorter ball, on leg. Pujara works it to the leg side for one.
Shorter ball, outside off. Kohli looks to push it away but gets the inside edge back on the pads.

That has turned sharply! Tossed up, outside off. It lands in the rough and turns back in. Kohli looks to block but the ball goes through the gate and goes just over the stumps. Even the keeper cannot collect it and the batters get a bye.
Flatter ball, outside off. Pushed to covers.
Flatter ball, outside off. Left alone.
Shorter ball, on off. Kohli works it off the back foot to deep mid-wicket for one.
Cheteshwar Pujara comes down the track and clips it past square leg for another single.
Loopy ball, on off. Kohli gets on the front foot and blocks it.
Shorter ball, on off. Kohli works it towards short leg.
Tossed up, outside off. Kohli drives it hard to the fielder at deep extra cover.
Flatter ball, on off. Worked to the leg side.
Shorter ball, on off. Kohli stays back and works it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up, outside off. Kohli gets to the pitch of the ball and pushes it to deep cover for one.
Flatter ball, outside off. Pujara offers his pads after striding forward.
Shorter ball, outside off. Cut away to deep cover for one.
Shorter again, outside off. Pushed to mid off now.
Shorter ball, on off. Kohli goes back and works it past square leg for one.
Flatter ball, on off. Pushed to deep cover for one. That brings up 200 for India.
Loopy ball, around off. Pujara stays in his crease and blocks it.
Tossed up, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara looks to defend with his bat and pad together. The ball goes towards short leg, who takes it, but it came off the pad.
Flatter ball, on leg. Worked to the leg side.
Shorter ball, on off. Pushed to the off side.
Tossed up, outside off. Pujara gets to the pitch and then leaves it.
Shorter ball, on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, outside off. Kohli drives it to deep cover for one.
Cheteshwar Pujara comes down the track and taps it to the off side for one.
Loopy ball, on off. Pushed back to the bowler.
FOUR! Short ball and punished! Root bowls the leg spinner now, but he bowls it very short. Kohli goes back in his crease and pulls it past deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Tossed up, on off. Kohli blocks it out.
FOUR! Almost takes out the umpire this time! How's the light now, Root? Short ball, on leg. Pujara pulls it hard. The square leg umpire sways away from it in time and the ball races to the fence.
Loopy ball, on leg. Worked to the leg side.
Flatter ball, around off. Punched away.
Flatter ball, way outside off. Pujara leaves it.
This stays low! Loopy ball, outside off. Pujara plays for the spin but the ball goes straight and stays a bit low. Buttler cannot collect it and the batters get two byes.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, on off. Kohli gets forward and blocks it.
Tossed up, outside off. Kohli gets in a good stride and blocks it.
Flatter ball, on off. Blocked out.
Shorter ball, on off. Kohli works it to the leg side for one.
Cheteshwar Pujara comes down the track and drives it through covers. The man from deep cover runs to his right and dives to keep it to two. Cheteshwar Pujara moves into the 90s now.
Tossed up, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara comes down the track and pads it away.
Anderson is right on the button! Starts with serving it on a length close to off, shaping away, Kohli shoulders arms.
In the channel outside off, on a length again, not much movement on this occasion, Virat has nothing to do with it as he leaves it alone.
Anderson is sticking to the line outside off, a gentle away movement on this occasion, Kohli continues to leave it.
Jimmy keeps probing around off. Close to off and shapes away after landing on a length, Kohli covers his stumps and allows it through.
Another good delivery and another good leave from the Indian captain. On and around off, moving away off the seam, Kohli is very patient at the moment.

Anderson makes Kohli play. Serves it on middle and off, Kohli plays late and drops it with gentle hands in front of the cordon. Looks for a run but a loud shout of no comes from Pujara. Day 4 begins with a maiden over.
Robinson delivers it very full and around off, Pujara pushes it out from the bottom half of his bat to covers. He is on 91 and would love to get a hundred and end his lean patch.
Fuller in length and outside off, there is a hint of away movement, Pujara watches the line closely and then makes a leave.
Fuller again, a bit close to off but not close enough to bother the batsman. It lands and moves away, Cheteshwar Pujara just sees it through to the keeper.
Oohhh...that wasn't too far away from the off pole. Robinson lands it on a good length and close to off, this one just holds its line and Pujara allows it through. Brave leave in the end.
Slips a full ball down the leg side, Pujara tries to flick but misses.
Ollie Robinson returns to bowl in the channel outside off, shaping away off the seam, Pujara is forward to cover the line as he makes a leave. A couple of maidens to begin the day's play.
Anderson bowls it on a good length and in the corridor outside off, Kohli shoulders arms.
Anderson gets close to the off stump line this time, Kohli does well to cover his stumps as he allows it through.
Anderson remains disciplined in his approach, bowling it in the channel outside off, an outswinger, Kohli also stays disciplined as he leaves.
Angles it in around off and takes it away with the seam movement, Virat lifts his bat and allows it through to the keeper.
Identical to the last delivery, Anderson is playing on Kohli's patience here. Virat is in no mood to commit himself to any kind of a shot.
On a length and close to off, it straightens from there, Kohli has to play at that and he taps it down to point. Third maiden of the morning.
Angling in from around off, Pujara has his defensive bat down as he keeps it out safely to mid-wicket.
On a good length around off, Pujara defends it from the back foot back towards the bowler. Unlike Anderson, Ollie is making the batsman play more.

OUT! PUJARA IS GONE! Robinson has hit the jackpot. He comes up with a full delivery around off, shaping back in, Pujara offers no shot and takes it on his back pad. They appeal but the umpire stays still. Root has a word with his bowler and the keeper. This time he goes for the referral in time. Remember, the impact won't be an issue here as the batter was not offering any shot. The Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows three reds. Huge roar from the English players, they have got an early success this morning and it's the big wicket of Pujara. Surely, there was an error in judgement from Cheteshwar Pujara, he was undone first by the fuller length and then by the extravagant inward movement. To worsen the situation, he was hit on the back pad. Had that been on the front pad, it could have headed over the stumps. Once again he misses out on scoring a century.
Howout: lbw b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Good first ball to Ajinkya. On a length and close to off, Rahane defends it from the inside half of his bat to the leg side.
On middle and leg, shaping down, Rahane tries to flick but it takes his pads and deflects down to fine leg for a leg bye. There's the first run for India this morning.
Fullish and just outside off, Kohli allows it through to the keeper. Called a no ball for overstepping.
Around off on a good length, Kohli defends it from the back foot to the off side.
It's on a length and around off, Rahane defends it from the back foot to the off side.
Rahane gets off the mark. On a good length around off, Rahane pushes it defensively to the off side, finds the gap at covers and crosses for a run.
Beaten all ends up! Anderson dishes it out around off, on a fuller length and gets it to move away, Kohli commits himself on the front foot, tries to push inside the line and is beaten.
Inward movement on this delivery, it starts from a length around middle, Virat fails to work it around and is hit on the pads. They cross for a leg bye.
Lands it on a length and just outside off, a good leave by Rahane.
Anderson targets the stumps with an inswinger, landing on a length around off, Rahane meets it with a dead bat as he blocks it from the crease.
On a fullish length, outside off, shapes away as the Indian captain makes a leave.
First runs for Virat Kohli this morning! On a length, angling in, around off, Kohli drops this to the cover region and crosses ends.
Lands it on a length, in the fourth stump channel, the ball jags back in quickly, as Ajinkya Rahane taps this one to the off side.
FOUR! Confident shot from Rahane and this is the first boundary of the morning. Overpitched delivery, closer to off, Ajinkya Rahane pushes this one gently through the mid off region for a boundary.
Outside off, it lands and shapes away, AR makes no movement to play at this as he leaves.
Around off, on a length, Ajinkya defends this one out solidly.
Closer to off, length this time, Virat just dabs this one towards point.

BEATEN! Wonderful delivery from Jimmy. This was a similar delivery to Virat's first-innings dismissal. Fuller in length, around off, the ball shapes away late as Virat Kohli looks to play straight, but he fails to get bat on ball this time.

SHOUT FOR AN LBW! Back of a length, around off, Virat Kohli looks to defend, but the ball shoots up and hits Kohli high on the thigh pad. An appeal but turned down. Jimmy does not want the review. Root is looking around, hoping that someone will persuade him to take the review, but it does not happen. A good decision as the replays show that the ball was missing the wickets.
Around off, pushed to covers this time.
In the fourth stump channel, length, Virat Kohli shoulders arms this time.

NOT OUT! A brilliant decision to take the review and the on-field decision has been overturned. England were over the moon but they have to be brought back here. The sound was off Virat's bat hitting his pad, not off the ball coming off the edge. On a length this time, in the zone of uncertainty outside off, Virat Kohli looks to push at this but the ball whistles through to Buttler, who takes it and appeals. The umpire raises his finger and the roof has been raised at Leeds. Virat Kohli turns around and looks to walk back, but he turns as Ajinkya Rahane from the other end persuades him to take the review. Virat is unsure if he edged that. The replays roll in and it turned out really well for India, as UltraEdge shows that Kohli hit his bat to his pad and there was no edge. Kohli survives.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Outside off, left alone by Rahane.
FOUR! Wow! Well played by Rahane. A half-volley, around off this time, Ajinkya Rahane gets low and drives this one wonderfully through the cover-point region for a boundary.
Around off, tapped to the off side.
Angled around off and middle, this is knocked to the mid on region.
Short of a length, on off, tapped to covers for one.
Ajinkya Rahane has just watchfully blocked this out.
Outside off, no shot offered.
On a length, outside off, Rahane looks to defend but gets beaten on this occasion.
Around off, fuller this time, Rahane prods ahead and pushes to covers.
Length, outside off, shaping inwards, Rahane lets this pass by him, to Buttler.

FOUR! Fifty for Virat Kohli! His first 50 of the series and he will be looking to turn this into a big one. Fuller-length ball, around off, Virat Kohli goes back and whips this through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Virat Kohli has just watchfully blocked this out.
Good-length ball, on off, tapped to point this time.
Good length again, fourth stump channel, Virat Kohli presses forward and hangs his bat in defense, but the ball shapes away late and beats the outside edge.

FOUR! Save your legs, that was going to race away to the boundary. Overpitched slightly, around off, Kohli shows the full face of the bat and beats the diving mid on fielder (James Anderson) to his left, with a punch and gets his second boundary of the over.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! There it is! You are never settled as a batter in England and even though Kohli just got to his fifty in this over, he has to depart. Joe Root takes the catch and it is quite poetic how the English skipper plays a part in removing the Indian captain. Root seems pretty happy with his work. Back of a length, just around the off pole, the ball lands and holds its line slightly as Virat Kohli looks to block this one out with an angled bat. The ball catches the outside edge and goes to the left of Joe Root at first slip, who moves that side and makes no mistake. Two quick wickets and India are on the back foot now. Both the overnight batters have been sent packing and England are smelling blood. India are still behind by 117 runs!
Howout: c Joe Root b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: On a length, close to off, Rahane stays back and taps it down to covers for a run.
Anderson delivers it on a good length, around middle, Pant is on the charge as he tries to defend. Misses the ball and is hit near the box. Is this smart batting or reckless?
Fuller this time, around middle and leg, Pant walks forward and flicks as his bat turns in his hands. The ball rolls in the gap at mid-wicket and they cross. Rishabh Pant is off the mark.
Around off on a length, the batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Fuller and on off, angling in, Rahane flicks it off his pads but finds mid-wicket.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Third wicket goes down for India this morning and England are celebrating big. Needless from Rahane. Anderson delivers it on a length and just outside off, it lands and moves away slightly, Rahane should have looked to defend it close to his body but needless hangs his bat out in defense. The ball moves away, takes a thick outside edge and goes to the keeper. As soon as Jos Buttler catches it, Joe Root jumps in delight. The crowd is loving it. India have now lost 5 wickets and staring down the barrel.
Howout: c Jos Buttler b James Anderson

Commentary: Swing and a miss! Pant will bat on his terms, regardless of the situation, he wants to attack the bowlers. Robinson angles across a shortish delivery, outside off, Pant jumps down the track, tries to slap it through the line but misses. Maybe, Rishabh Pant doesn't trust his defense enough to survive this moment.
On a length, around middle, this time Pant stays compact in his defense and blocks it down on the surface.
Around leg, on a length, Pant fails to work it around and is hit high on the pads.
Fuller, closer to off, Pant is standing outside the crease to smother the movement and defends it down.

OUT! CAUGHT AT SLIPS! Pant gets out defending. Hmm... Maybe, that's why he was swinging his bat. Ollie Robinson has shown great discipline this morning. His lines have been exemplary and he has altered his lengths superbly as well. This one is served in the channel outside off and the natural angle of the bowler takes it away from the left-hander.
