Pant could have left it alone but he wants to feel the ball. Goes after it with a defensive bat and edges it to third slip. Craig Overton has safe hands and England are four wickets away now from making it 1-1 in the series.
Howout: c Craig Overton b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Huge shout for an lbw, not given. A big inswinger from Robinson, landing on a good length and jagging back in sharply. Shami shuffles across a bit in defense but misses. He is rapped on the pads, they appeal but the finger stays down. Maybe, too high. End of a superb over by Robinson.
Around off, on a length, kept out by Jadeja.

FOUR! Good shot down the ground. Not a lot to be happy about for India, but this shot will lift the mood ever-so-slightly. On a length, around the off pole, Ravindra Jadeja just pushes this gently through mid off.
Fuller, way outside off, RJ shows no interest in playing at that.

EDGED AND FOUR! A bit streaky and this could have been the end of Jadeja too. On a length, angling away from around off, Ravindra Jadeja looks to drive but only manages an outside edge, which goes aerially past Moeen Ali at point, and runs away to the ropes. Moeen probably had all his weight on the left leg and hence didn't get enough time to react with a dive.
Fuller again, outside off, Jadeja leaves it untouched.
Another length ball way outside off, Ravindra shoulders arms on this occasion.

Again a shout for an lbw against Shami! Not given and England also decide not to review. Robinson angles in a length ball, around middle and leg, further going down, Shami tries to flick but misses. They put in an unsuccessful appeal. Missing leg, probably.

NOT OUT! Missing the leg stump. Identical to the last delivery, on a full length around middle and angling down, Shami again fails to flick and wears it on his pads. The appeal is made and this time the finger has gone up. Shami takes the referral. Nothing on the UltraEdge but the Ball Tracker confirms that it's missing the sticks.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Fuller and on middle, this time Shami uses the angle and flicks it through square leg for a couple of runs.
FOUR! Even better shot, in front of square leg this time. Robinson is straight in line, on a length, Shami flicks it with nice timing and sends it to the fence.
Drifting down the leg side, Shami tries to nudge it fine but fails to connect.
Tossed up ball landing full on middle, Jadeja knocks it down to long on for one. India trail by exactly 100 runs.

OUT! SOUND OF TIMBER! Shami is done for this Test match. Big turn for the off spinner. Moeen gives it a good toss and lands it on a fuller length outside off, it probably lands on one of the footmarks and breaks back in sharply. Shami tries to push it through the line by getting forward but it spins back in to beat his bat and goes on to shatter the stumps. England inching closer. Can they pick the remaining wickets before Lunch?
Howout: b Moeen Ali

Commentary: Flighted delivery, pitching full and close to off, Sharma is on the front foot as he blocks.
Fuller and around off, Sharma drives it through covers for a couple of runs.
A touch flatter this time, around off, Ishant goes back and defends it down to the off side.
Spinning back in from around off, Sharma stays back again and defends it down on the leg side, wide of short leg.
Lands it on a good length around off, Jadeja sticks on the back foot and defends it down on the surface.
Around off, length ball, this is nudged to the fielder at square leg.
Pitched up, outside off, Ravindra Jadeja keeps his wits about himself and lets the ball through.
Short-of-a-length delivery, banged on middle, RJ hops and tucks this to fine leg for a run.

OUT! EDGED AND CAUGHT! Wicket number 5 for Robinson and he is on fire! The Indian batters just keep following each other back to the shed. None of them are showing any sort of resistance. Ollie serves this on a length, closer to the off pole, makes Ishant have a poke at this, but the ball holds its line after landing. Kisses the outside edge and Jos Buttler has an easy catch. We are nearing the curtains on this game. Just 2 more wickets away, are the Three Lions!
Howout: c Jos Buttler b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Length-ball around off, this is kept out nicely by Bumrah as he strides forward. Another top over by Robinson!
Shortish, on the pads, Ravindra Jadeja nudges this one to the leg side. Finds backward square leg.
Floated, fuller and around off, Jadeja presses forward and defends it out.
Tosses up again, full around off, Ravindra Jadeja prods ahead and smothers the ball out.

SIX! Jadeja is not going to hang around. He will try to get some quick runs and apply some pressure on the English bowlers. This is bowled fuller again, around middle and spinning away, Ravindra Jadeja jumps out. Thwacks this one over the bowler for a biggie.
A single as this is tucked to the mid-wicket region.
Moeen tosses this one too, lands it around off, the ball hits the deck and spins in as Bumrah presses forward. The ball takes the inside edge, but hits Bumrah on his pad and falls safely on the deck.
Slants a length delivery across the southpaw, an easy leave for Jadeja.
An action replay of the previous delivery.
Around off, fuller, pushed to the cover region.

FOUR! That's played nicely. Jadeja is getting some boundaries here, but it does not look like it will make any substantial difference. Overpitched this time, on off, Jadeja punches this with hard hands through the mid off region.

FOUR! Another good shot. Placed it nicely this time. Slightly short, outside off, angling away, he waits for the ball to come to him and just pushes this one past the gully fielder. Jadeja wants to save India at least from the embarrassment of an innings defeat. Can he do it?

FOUR! Third in a row! Craig Overton comes 'round the wicket and hurls a shortish ball, offering width outside off, Jadeja again waits for the ball to arrive and then just dabs it past the diving gully fielder. India are behind by 78, whereas, England need 2 more wickets.
Loopy, landing full on off, spins in, Bumrah gets low and slog-sweeps it to deep mid-wicket for a run.
Short, on off, tapped to the point region.
Short again, width offered outside off, slapped to sweeper cover for one. Hands the strike back to Bumrah.
Tossed up, outside off, this is jammed out to the off side.
A touch short of fuller length, around off, Bumrah dabs it back onto the deck.
Flighted on off, Bumrah looks to defend, but the ball catches the outside edge and runs away wide of first slip. He wants one but Jadeja, rightfully, sends him back.

OUT! EDGED AND CAUGHT! Overton joins the party now! Brilliant work from him and another Indian batter takes a sad, long walk back to the shed. Jadeja walks back and there goes India's last shot at avoiding an innings defeat. On a length by Overton, landing closer to off and then leaving the batter. Ravindra Jadeja looks to defend but that proves to be his undoing, as the outside edge is caught. Another catch that Jos Buttler is not going to drop. England are one more wicket away from levelling the series.
Howout: c Jos Buttler b Craig Overton

Commentary: Overton slips this down the leg side, Siraj tries to flick but misses.

OUT! EDGED AND CAUGHT! It is all done! There is the game. It has not taken long for England in the morning session on Day 4 to wrap the game up. Brilliant work from England and Overton finishes proceedings. Craig Overton bowls this one on a length, closer to the off pole, it lands and shapes away. Mohammed Siraj looks to block but the outside edge is induced. Jonny Bairstow, at second slip, dives to his right and pouches this. ENGLAND WIN BY AN INNINGS AND 76 RUNS AND LEVEL THE SERIES 1-1!
Howout: c Jonny Bairstow b Craig Overton
